1
00:00:23,754 --> 00:00:25,713
(pager beeping)

2
00:00:36,016 --> 00:00:39,352
- How's my mother doing?
- Not so good today.

3
00:00:47,402 --> 00:00:49,612
(woman on PA)

4
00:01:02,668 --> 00:01:04,877
Why weren't you in here before?

5
00:01:05,045 --> 00:01:07,296
- (man) The doctor said...
- Screw the doctor.

6
00:01:08,507 --> 00:01:09,549
Mom.

7
00:01:11,218 --> 00:01:14,137
- You should save your strength.
- Jack, if I go...

8
00:01:14,263 --> 00:01:16,472
Mom, you're not going to go.

9
00:01:16,598 --> 00:01:19,892
If I go, I want you
to make me a promise.

10
00:01:23,856 --> 00:01:26,399
- Say, "I promise."
- I promise.

11
00:01:26,567 --> 00:01:28,067
That you'll always love me.

12
00:01:30,070 --> 00:01:31,070
Of course, Mom.

13
00:01:31,196 --> 00:01:33,447
And you'll never get married.

14
00:01:35,117 --> 00:01:37,410
Mom, no, no.

15
00:01:37,578 --> 00:01:39,787
I can't promise that.

16
00:01:39,913 --> 00:01:44,292
No girl could love you like I did, Jack.
You'll be unhappy. Don't do it.

17
00:01:44,918 --> 00:01:47,170
- Mom, don't say that.
- (knuckles crack)

18
00:01:47,296 --> 00:01:49,922
Promise me, Jack. Never.

19
00:01:50,507 --> 00:01:52,592
Mom, that's a huge thing to ask.

20
00:01:53,677 --> 00:01:55,595
Mom... Mom!

21
00:01:55,721 --> 00:01:57,930
Mom! Mom!

22
00:01:58,807 --> 00:02:02,268
Mom, come back!
I promise I won't get married!

23
00:02:03,770 --> 00:02:05,688
(musical medley plays)

24
00:04:11,273 --> 00:04:14,025
(Jack) That's Mrs. Lupo
with the cable installer.

25
00:04:14,151 --> 00:04:17,820
I'm Jack Singer, and I was hired
by Mrs. Lupo's paranoid husband,

26
00:04:17,946 --> 00:04:20,156
who turned out
not to be so paranoid.

27
00:04:20,282 --> 00:04:23,034
I feel for the guy. I really do.

28
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:25,369
I feel for all these people,
men and women,

29
00:04:25,495 --> 00:04:28,831
the cheaters and cheated on,
sneaking around hotel lobbies

30
00:04:28,957 --> 00:04:30,916
looking over their shoulders.

31
00:04:31,084 --> 00:04:35,588
I'm sorry, but they only confirm what
my crazy mother said about marriage:

32
00:04:35,756 --> 00:04:38,257
That it's a disaster waiting to happen.

33
00:04:38,383 --> 00:04:40,259
Although my job can get depressing,

34
00:04:40,385 --> 00:04:42,094
at least it's not dangerous,

35
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:44,430
and I do hear some great stories.

36
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,933
My wife is having an affair
with Mike Tyson.

37
00:04:51,146 --> 00:04:52,688
"Mike Tyson" Mike Tyson?

38
00:04:52,814 --> 00:04:54,774
Yeah.

39
00:04:56,318 --> 00:04:59,111
That's her. That's Millie.

40
00:05:00,989 --> 00:05:04,992
Well, she's a beautiful girl.

41
00:05:05,118 --> 00:05:09,205
- When I think of the two of 'em!
- All right. Calm down. Calm down.

42
00:05:09,331 --> 00:05:11,040
Let's just think this through.

43
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:15,336
Now, my first question, obviously:

44
00:05:15,462 --> 00:05:17,630
- You've seen them together?
- What?

45
00:05:17,798 --> 00:05:21,175
You've seen them together?
Your wife and Mr. Tyson?

46
00:05:22,135 --> 00:05:24,136
- You don't believe me either!
- Of course I believe you.

47
00:05:24,262 --> 00:05:27,139
- I just need a place to start.
- Everybody thinks I'm nuts!

48
00:05:27,307 --> 00:05:29,475
The guys at the plant. Everybody.

49
00:05:29,601 --> 00:05:33,020
They tell me she's sneaking with
Freddy Ramirez at the Sunrise Motel,

50
00:05:33,146 --> 00:05:35,147
but I know it's the champ.

51
00:05:35,273 --> 00:05:36,690
She wouldn't cheat with a piece of shit

52
00:05:36,817 --> 00:05:39,276
like Freddy Ramirez,
beautiful girl like that.

53
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:43,489
I'm sure you're right.
Don't get me wrong, OK?

54
00:05:43,615 --> 00:05:46,826
But, hey, for openers, let's say
I follow this Ramirez around...

55
00:05:46,993 --> 00:05:49,161
Make sure it's not him.

56
00:05:49,287 --> 00:05:51,372
- You're all the same.
- Mr. Tomashefsky.

57
00:05:51,498 --> 00:05:54,583
- Nobody believes me.
- Don't just take off.

58
00:05:56,461 --> 00:05:59,547
I'm sure it's hard to talk about,
but I'm a good listener!

59
00:05:59,673 --> 00:06:01,006
Mr. Tomashefsky!

60
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:04,260
- Leave me alone!
- Hi, Bob.

61
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:07,972
(Jack) It's not glamorous work,
that's the bottom line.

62
00:06:08,098 --> 00:06:09,640
So why am I
telling you all of this?

63
00:06:10,392 --> 00:06:12,977
Because I do have
an amazing story to tell

64
00:06:13,103 --> 00:06:16,021
about me and my girlfriend,
Betsy Nolan.

65
00:06:16,189 --> 00:06:19,567
She teaches second grade
at the Skelton School in Manhattan,

66
00:06:19,693 --> 00:06:21,569
and she's the love of my life.

67
00:06:21,695 --> 00:06:25,197
- I just haven't been able to marry her.
- Milton moved out?

68
00:06:25,365 --> 00:06:27,199
(woman) Thursday.

69
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:30,077
I had ordered Chinese,
and he says, "Chinese again?"

70
00:06:30,203 --> 00:06:33,038
Then he comes out
with his suitcase already packed!

71
00:06:33,206 --> 00:06:37,001
I know David's been very quiet.
I thought that something was wrong.

72
00:06:38,128 --> 00:06:41,088
Listen, Judy, if there's
anything that I can do...

73
00:06:41,214 --> 00:06:44,091
Thanks. I thought it was important
that you know.

74
00:06:44,217 --> 00:06:45,426
I'm so sorry.

75
00:06:47,137 --> 00:06:49,263
- Bye, David.
- Bye.

76
00:06:49,389 --> 00:06:51,307
- (Betsy) See you tomorrow, OK?
- OK.

77
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,476
- Bye.
- Come on, sweetie.

78
00:06:53,602 --> 00:06:57,188
- (Jack) I was in the neighborhood.
- What a nice surprise.

79
00:06:58,565 --> 00:07:02,735
Oh. Forgot about that.
Tough day, huh?

80
00:07:02,903 --> 00:07:06,530
It's so awful. And besides David,
they have a two-year old.

81
00:07:06,656 --> 00:07:08,782
- That's my point.
- About what?

82
00:07:08,909 --> 00:07:10,576
People get married, and then they do

83
00:07:10,702 --> 00:07:13,078
the most hideous,
unbelievable things to each other.

84
00:07:13,246 --> 00:07:16,957
Not all people. Come on, Jack.
That's your mother talking.

85
00:07:19,085 --> 00:07:22,379
- I dreamt about her again last night.
- Was she naked again?

86
00:07:22,506 --> 00:07:25,174
Hey, I only had one dream
where she was naked.

87
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:27,468
- She was vacuuming.
- Still...

88
00:07:27,594 --> 00:07:29,011
It wasn't sexual.

89
00:07:29,137 --> 00:07:31,680
- It was about cleanliness.
- (Betsy laughs)

90
00:07:31,806 --> 00:07:34,058
(Jack) She's so great.
When I play poker,

91
00:07:34,184 --> 00:07:37,186
she helps with the food,
and she's funny with the guys.

92
00:07:37,312 --> 00:07:42,399
Now, the ones with those pretty crowns,
they're called kings?

93
00:07:42,526 --> 00:07:44,610
Kidding!

94
00:07:44,736 --> 00:07:46,612
- Is she the best?
- She's the best.

95
00:07:46,780 --> 00:07:48,739
Now shut up already. Let's play.

96
00:07:48,865 --> 00:07:50,574
(Jack) And sometimes,
if she's off from school,

97
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:52,952
she'll go out with me on a tail job.

98
00:07:53,078 --> 00:07:57,122
OK, Rolexes, 35 dollars.
Downtown, they're 45.

99
00:07:57,249 --> 00:07:58,874
Bada-bing, bada-bang.

100
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,961
- There he is.
- That's him?

101
00:08:02,087 --> 00:08:05,673
- (woman, indistinct)
- That fat pig? And he has four kids?

102
00:08:05,799 --> 00:08:08,133
Just a little louder.
They might not have heard you.

103
00:08:08,301 --> 00:08:10,886
- I'm hungry. How about you?
- (Jack) Wait a beat.

104
00:08:12,597 --> 00:08:14,014
Now.

105
00:08:17,978 --> 00:08:21,522
This is very hard being inconspicuous.

106
00:08:21,648 --> 00:08:25,818
It's a gift. Your problem is you're much
too beautiful for this kind of work.

107
00:08:25,944 --> 00:08:29,196
Me? I'm everyman.

108
00:08:29,322 --> 00:08:30,656
Here we go.

109
00:08:32,367 --> 00:08:33,826
Oh, God.

110
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:40,249
Ugh! This is so depressing.

111
00:08:40,375 --> 00:08:43,002
But it doesn't mean that we'd
wind up like this, Jack, it doesn't.

112
00:08:43,169 --> 00:08:44,503
No. It doesn't.

113
00:08:47,882 --> 00:08:49,842
Jack, stop with your mother already.

114
00:08:49,968 --> 00:08:51,969
I try, but I can't.

115
00:08:52,762 --> 00:08:54,763
So why don't you go see a shrink?

116
00:08:55,849 --> 00:08:59,643
It's too much money,
and I prefer to work it out myself.

117
00:09:00,770 --> 00:09:05,190
- As long as you wait for me.
- Of course I'll wait for you.

118
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:09,445
Sometimes I'm afraid to go to sleep.

119
00:09:10,530 --> 00:09:12,197
Maybe you won't dream about her.

120
00:09:13,617 --> 00:09:18,245
- Maybe I'll just read.
- Come here, you big lug.

121
00:09:31,217 --> 00:09:33,385
(Jack) A year later,
things with Betsy and me...

122
00:09:33,553 --> 00:09:37,389
Well, they just started
to get very shaky.

123
00:09:38,433 --> 00:09:41,393
(Betsy on machine) I feel as if
I might be coming down with something.

124
00:09:41,519 --> 00:09:44,521
She was finding excuses
not to come over,

125
00:09:44,648 --> 00:09:47,441
and when she did,
things weren't the same.

126
00:09:48,526 --> 00:09:50,194
I'm losing her.

127
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:53,530
Speaking of losing, you owe me 50
from the Notre Dame game.

128
00:09:53,657 --> 00:09:57,284
- Sally, I love her.
- Love her or not, that's a different...

129
00:09:57,410 --> 00:09:59,495
Sally. Villanova-Georgetown.

130
00:09:59,621 --> 00:10:00,954
You want Georgetown,
you gotta give three.

131
00:10:01,081 --> 00:10:04,583
- Uptown, it's two and a half.
- Cha Cha, do me a favor. Bet uptown.

132
00:10:04,709 --> 00:10:06,710
Jack, if you love her, then marry her.

133
00:10:06,836 --> 00:10:10,255
It's not the end of the world.
The decline, yes, but not the end.

134
00:10:10,423 --> 00:10:12,841
- Thanks very much.
- Ask anybody.

135
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:17,221
- She's different.
- I repeat... Ask anybody.

136
00:10:18,932 --> 00:10:21,225
(ltalian music plays)

137
00:10:30,610 --> 00:10:33,862
- This isn't good, Jack.
- Order something else.

138
00:10:34,948 --> 00:10:36,198
I'm talking about us.

139
00:10:38,785 --> 00:10:42,705
- We're just going through a down phase.
- No, it's bigger than that.

140
00:10:44,249 --> 00:10:47,459
I feel like I'm counting on something
that may never happen.

141
00:10:48,294 --> 00:10:50,963
Jack, we have to go to the next step.

142
00:10:52,966 --> 00:10:55,634
Is this, like, an ultimatum?

143
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:59,138
No, I'm just telling you
that I won't be a girlfriend forever.

144
00:10:59,305 --> 00:11:02,891
There's too much that I want.
I want kids and a family.

145
00:11:03,935 --> 00:11:06,311
Jack, I've got to know
what the deal is with us.

146
00:11:07,397 --> 00:11:10,107
- I'm in love with you.
- And I'm in love with you.

147
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:13,360
But I need a commitment.
Life's too short.

148
00:11:14,654 --> 00:11:16,572
I want to be married.

149
00:11:23,621 --> 00:11:25,539
(thunder cracks)

150
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:29,334
(Betsy) Light's green.

151
00:11:29,461 --> 00:11:31,044
(Jack) Let's get married tomorrow.

152
00:11:32,172 --> 00:11:35,257
Let's just do it... get on a plane,
go to Vegas and do it.

153
00:11:35,383 --> 00:11:37,217
- Now.
- (cars honking)

154
00:11:38,219 --> 00:11:41,555
- You're serious?
- I must be. My legs are paralyzed.

155
00:11:41,681 --> 00:11:43,599
Oh, sweetie!

156
00:11:43,725 --> 00:11:45,684
(Jack) The die was cast.

157
00:11:45,852 --> 00:11:49,188
If I had just said "city hall,"
the story would end here,

158
00:11:49,355 --> 00:11:53,108
but I didn't, and Betsy and I
took our fateful trip to Vegas.

159
00:11:53,234 --> 00:11:54,234
(♪ Bruce Springsteen: Viva! Las Vegas)

160
00:12:09,959 --> 00:12:11,168
(car honks)

161
00:12:37,403 --> 00:12:40,739
(Jack) The man in the limo
was Tommy Korman, the gambler,

162
00:12:40,907 --> 00:12:43,450
and he was about
to enter my life.

163
00:12:45,745 --> 00:12:48,372
Yep. Home, sweet home.

164
00:12:51,584 --> 00:12:53,377
How you doin'?

165
00:12:53,503 --> 00:12:56,046
(Elvises chattering)

166
00:12:58,258 --> 00:13:00,425
I was with two fine-looking
women last night.

167
00:13:00,552 --> 00:13:02,886
One was so fine.
She reminded me of Debra Paget.

168
00:13:03,012 --> 00:13:05,138
She made Debra Paget
look like a boy.

169
00:13:05,265 --> 00:13:06,723
What?

170
00:13:07,934 --> 00:13:10,394
Look at all these Elvises here.
It looks like a friggin' zoo.

171
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,771
- It's a freakin' zoo.
- (man) Mr. Korman!

172
00:13:13,815 --> 00:13:17,943
Mr. Korman, Mr. Sandwich,
Buddy Walker. Welcome to Bally's.

173
00:13:18,111 --> 00:13:21,572
I've replaced Tony Carmelo.
I didn't know if you'd heard.

174
00:13:22,949 --> 00:13:24,908
It escaped my attention.

175
00:13:25,034 --> 00:13:26,702
I wondered if I could
have a word with you.

176
00:13:26,828 --> 00:13:28,579
It's all right.

177
00:13:28,705 --> 00:13:30,956
- Yeah. Sure.
- Yeah.

178
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:36,295
- Tommy, we have a small problem.
- Oh, yeah?

179
00:13:36,462 --> 00:13:39,882
Penthouse A is not available, but...

180
00:13:40,008 --> 00:13:42,009
- Oh?
- (Buddy groans)

181
00:13:42,135 --> 00:13:45,220
Buddy? I would like Penthouse A,

182
00:13:45,346 --> 00:13:48,640
where I've stayed for 15 years,
made up for me now.

183
00:13:48,766 --> 00:13:49,850
(machines chiming)

184
00:13:49,976 --> 00:13:52,978
The president of Brazil is in there.

185
00:13:53,146 --> 00:13:56,648
I don't care if Ming the Friggin'
Merciless is in there. Get him out.

186
00:13:56,774 --> 00:13:57,816
OK?

187
00:13:59,152 --> 00:14:00,861
- Will do.
- Good.

188
00:14:02,238 --> 00:14:05,741
Now I shake your hand.
That's great, Buddy.

189
00:14:14,459 --> 00:14:17,294
(woman on PA) Welcome to McCarran
Field, Las Vegas, Nevada...

190
00:14:17,420 --> 00:14:20,380
the family fun capital of America.

191
00:14:20,506 --> 00:14:23,133
- Good luck.
- We just got here!

192
00:14:23,259 --> 00:14:26,637
Oh, my God!

193
00:14:26,971 --> 00:14:28,764
(swimmers chattering)

194
00:14:31,768 --> 00:14:36,355
Oof! This is some heat.
It's got to be 110, easy.

195
00:14:36,481 --> 00:14:38,065
No, but it's dry.

196
00:14:38,191 --> 00:14:39,691
That's what these schmucks say.

197
00:14:39,817 --> 00:14:41,318
- "150, but it's dry."
- Yeah.

198
00:14:41,444 --> 00:14:43,570
So hot you friggin' can't see straight.

199
00:14:43,696 --> 00:14:46,281
Excuse me, gentlemen.
Would you like chaises?

200
00:14:46,407 --> 00:14:47,950
- What?
- Chaises.

201
00:14:48,076 --> 00:14:50,285
- Chaises?
- Yes, sir.

202
00:14:50,411 --> 00:14:53,789
- What's your name?
- Gary, sir.

203
00:14:53,915 --> 00:14:57,292
Well, "Gary sir," do you understand
that there's no more ozone layer left?

204
00:14:57,418 --> 00:14:59,378
That you could get arrested
for friggin' manslaughter,

205
00:14:59,504 --> 00:15:01,672
lettin' people lay out here?

206
00:15:01,798 --> 00:15:03,757
- You find that funny?
- No, sir.

207
00:15:03,883 --> 00:15:05,717
(woman on PA) May I have
your attention...

208
00:15:05,885 --> 00:15:07,344
Here. Remember that, all right?

209
00:15:08,721 --> 00:15:10,180
(Gary) Thank you, sir.

210
00:15:10,306 --> 00:15:12,557
(exhales deeply)

211
00:15:12,684 --> 00:15:16,812
- Remember Donna and her sunbaths?
- Yeah. Who knew back then?

212
00:15:17,897 --> 00:15:19,856
Yeah. Who knew?

213
00:15:27,031 --> 00:15:30,325
Vegas. Miami. Wherever.

214
00:15:31,411 --> 00:15:34,287
She'd lay out there all day
with them Sidney Sheldon books...

215
00:15:34,414 --> 00:15:36,373
and her coconut oil.

216
00:15:38,751 --> 00:15:42,087
Doctor said they never saw skin
like that, like a saddlebag.

217
00:15:48,928 --> 00:15:51,722
- We got a game tonight?
- No. Not yet.

218
00:15:53,224 --> 00:15:55,350
- It's OK.
- Tommy...

219
00:15:56,769 --> 00:15:59,896
- She was a great girl, Donna.
- Yeah.

220
00:16:00,023 --> 00:16:02,107
I should've got her out of the sun.

221
00:16:04,110 --> 00:16:06,778
Twelve bucks!
No air-conditioning either.

222
00:16:06,904 --> 00:16:09,656
- I ain't going to tip him.
- Hound dog can't even speak English.

223
00:16:09,782 --> 00:16:12,284
(Betsy and Jack chuckling)

224
00:16:12,410 --> 00:16:14,619
I gotta get a suit like that.

225
00:16:18,416 --> 00:16:21,043
- That was some fighter.
- Yeah, that was some fighter.

226
00:16:22,128 --> 00:16:24,129
He knocked down Holmes twice.

227
00:16:24,255 --> 00:16:26,923
Twice. Hey, Tommy,
let's go say "hi," no?

228
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:29,593
- Go ahead.
- Hey, champ, how you doing?

229
00:16:29,719 --> 00:16:31,470
- You look great. How you doing?
- Real good.

230
00:16:31,637 --> 00:16:33,388
What about that Holmes fight
the other day? What happened?

231
00:16:33,514 --> 00:16:35,682
When Holmes went...
What'd he do?

232
00:16:35,808 --> 00:16:37,142
Wham.

233
00:16:58,039 --> 00:16:59,498
What, what, what?

234
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:02,709
Look over there.

235
00:17:05,171 --> 00:17:07,798
- It's unbelievable.
- Everything.

236
00:17:07,924 --> 00:17:11,176
Her legs. It's Donna.

237
00:17:14,347 --> 00:17:16,181
Look at all those Indian Elvises.

238
00:17:16,307 --> 00:17:18,683
Yeah, they loved
his movie Blue Calcutta.

239
00:17:18,810 --> 00:17:20,268
Come here.

240
00:17:21,354 --> 00:17:23,271
This is unbelievable.

241
00:17:23,397 --> 00:17:24,606
You're unbelievable.

242
00:17:24,732 --> 00:17:27,776
I want to get you in that room,
tear the bedspread off...

243
00:17:27,902 --> 00:17:30,237
Yoo-hoo! Can I get a room?

244
00:17:30,363 --> 00:17:33,448
This is God
giving me a second chance.

245
00:17:33,574 --> 00:17:35,158
There is no doubt about it.

246
00:17:36,202 --> 00:17:38,286
- What if they're married?
- Look at them.

247
00:17:39,163 --> 00:17:41,039
There's no way they're married.

248
00:17:49,048 --> 00:17:51,550
- (Betsy) Yikes.
- (both chuckle)

249
00:17:53,803 --> 00:17:58,056
Oh, my God. Jack!

250
00:17:58,224 --> 00:18:01,017
- We can't afford this!
- I got a deal through Sally Molars.

251
00:18:01,144 --> 00:18:04,521
120 bucks a night.
Is this great or what?

252
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,459
(Betsy sighs)

253
00:18:34,302 --> 00:18:36,303
What'd you think of that mirror?

254
00:18:37,889 --> 00:18:39,097
I liked it.

255
00:18:39,932 --> 00:18:43,185
I never realized
I had such a beautiful, round behind.

256
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:46,646
Or was that you?

257
00:18:46,772 --> 00:18:48,440
That might've been me.

258
00:18:54,363 --> 00:18:56,281
It's 2:30 already.

259
00:19:00,578 --> 00:19:04,915
Well, maybe we should get some lunch,
do a little gambling...

260
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:08,084
...and then get...

261
00:19:10,296 --> 00:19:13,381
I'm very happy.
I want you to know that.

262
00:19:13,507 --> 00:19:16,051
And I love you so, so much.

263
00:19:16,177 --> 00:19:18,637
Oh, I'm glad.

264
00:19:20,431 --> 00:19:22,057
- (water running)
- (slider opens)

265
00:19:28,272 --> 00:19:32,025
Yeah. Hi. This is Jack Singer
in the Ali Baba Suite.

266
00:19:32,151 --> 00:19:35,487
Yeah, you can take the "Do Not Disturb"
off my phone now. Thanks.

267
00:19:54,674 --> 00:19:58,677
(woman on PA) May I have your attention,
please. Bally's is happy to introduce...

268
00:19:58,803 --> 00:20:01,554
There's a poker game
for new guests, 4:00 to 6:00.

269
00:20:01,681 --> 00:20:05,225
That could be fun.
You could get a swim. I play.

270
00:20:05,351 --> 00:20:07,936
- And then we're off.
- Where should we go?

271
00:20:08,062 --> 00:20:11,690
They have all these chapels.
We'll just pick the most outrageous one.

272
00:20:12,441 --> 00:20:14,401
Your hand is wet.

273
00:20:15,194 --> 00:20:17,070
I'm nervous, but I'm OK.

274
00:20:17,196 --> 00:20:19,322
I want to do this.

275
00:20:19,448 --> 00:20:23,201
- Maybe we should go now.
- In this heat? It's 108 degrees.

276
00:20:23,369 --> 00:20:27,539
Come on. No, no, no, we waited
this long, we should do it right.

277
00:20:27,707 --> 00:20:30,083
Wait till the sun sets.
Get dressed up.

278
00:20:30,876 --> 00:20:34,379
- Jack, please.
- It's not just another excuse.

279
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:36,631
Hey.

280
00:20:36,757 --> 00:20:40,468
- We're here to get married.
- And to be together.

281
00:20:40,594 --> 00:20:42,220
Absolutely.

282
00:20:42,346 --> 00:20:44,889
So why do you have to play poker?

283
00:20:45,016 --> 00:20:47,225
Let's just hang out together.

284
00:20:47,393 --> 00:20:49,728
It'll relax me.
It's a fast game with some yokels.

285
00:20:49,854 --> 00:20:51,771
I'll probably make enough
to pay for the whole trip.

286
00:20:51,897 --> 00:20:54,649
Listen. It's right here,
$1,000 dollars in credits,

287
00:20:54,775 --> 00:20:57,694
so you're, like, covered
if you get murdered on a hand.

288
00:20:57,820 --> 00:21:01,990
This is just a promotional thing,
basically. Relax.

289
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:07,495
It's two hours.
Then we get married. End of story.

290
00:21:09,081 --> 00:21:11,041
I don't know.

291
00:21:13,586 --> 00:21:15,795
Really glad you could make it...
Jack, right?

292
00:21:15,921 --> 00:21:18,006
Yeah. It's my pleasure.

293
00:21:18,132 --> 00:21:19,924
You know, with all these Elvises...

294
00:21:20,092 --> 00:21:21,343
- Excuse me...
- (clears throat)

295
00:21:21,469 --> 00:21:23,762
Excuse me, Elvises running around, no?

296
00:21:23,888 --> 00:21:26,639
I haven't seen so many sideburns
since West Side Story.

297
00:21:29,602 --> 00:21:34,189
That's very funny. Wait.
That's New York wit. Am I right?

298
00:21:34,315 --> 00:21:36,274
New York wit?

299
00:21:37,610 --> 00:21:42,405
So, Tommy, you organize this
for the hotel? The game?

300
00:21:43,282 --> 00:21:45,909
Right. I'm...

301
00:21:46,035 --> 00:21:48,995
I'm retired from the dress business,
and I basically play for fun.

302
00:21:49,121 --> 00:21:53,458
And the hotel asked me
to help make the guests feel at home.

303
00:21:53,626 --> 00:21:56,419
- So a two-hour card game.
- Nobody gets too badly hurt.

304
00:21:56,545 --> 00:21:59,589
- Sure.
- Come on, come on. Let's play.

305
00:21:59,715 --> 00:22:03,885
The natives are getting restless.
So we'd better get going.

306
00:22:11,102 --> 00:22:14,938
(woman on PA) Telephone call
for Betsy Nolan. Betsy Nolan.

307
00:22:21,695 --> 00:22:25,407
Excuse... Jack, would you like me
to turn up the air-conditioning?

308
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:28,159
- No, thanks.
- Sure?

309
00:22:28,285 --> 00:22:29,577
(Jack) Yeah. I'm fine.

310
00:22:31,747 --> 00:22:33,832
See the raise.

311
00:22:34,583 --> 00:22:36,251
Bump 20.

312
00:22:37,336 --> 00:22:39,504
Can't catch a break here.

313
00:22:39,672 --> 00:22:42,507
- Get me a sandwich or something.
- Yes, sir.

314
00:22:43,551 --> 00:22:46,386
- I see it.
- (Tommy) Well, boys...

315
00:22:46,512 --> 00:22:48,847
the good Lord was kind enough
to bless me with a full boat.

316
00:22:48,973 --> 00:22:50,849
Fives overjacks.

317
00:22:50,975 --> 00:22:55,270
- Shit.
- Well, the King is out, boys.

318
00:22:59,191 --> 00:23:02,026
I have $20 left.
I probably should go.

319
00:23:02,153 --> 00:23:06,865
Personally, I think you're playing
very well. It's just some bad luck.

320
00:23:06,991 --> 00:23:10,034
You're playing perfect.
Just some bad luck.

321
00:23:10,161 --> 00:23:12,871
Look, guys,
I don't have this kind of money to lose.

322
00:23:12,997 --> 00:23:15,707
What really concerns me here,
Jack, is you're gonna go back

323
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:18,960
to New York
with a bad feeling about Vegas.

324
00:23:19,086 --> 00:23:22,964
- That concerns me.
- I really won't.

325
00:23:23,090 --> 00:23:25,175
He's scared. That's natural.

326
00:23:25,301 --> 00:23:27,719
(Jack) Hey, look, it's not a matter
of being scared, OK?

327
00:23:29,388 --> 00:23:31,890
What? It's just money?

328
00:23:32,016 --> 00:23:35,894
- Yeah. It's just money.
- Well.

329
00:23:36,061 --> 00:23:39,481
Tell you what. Here.
You just activated your line of credit.

330
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:42,817
Here's a thousand.

331
00:23:42,943 --> 00:23:46,613
You lose it, it's on the hotel.
You win it, you pay it back. Fair?

332
00:23:46,739 --> 00:23:49,407
Well, this afternoon
he wanted to play in this poker game...

333
00:23:49,533 --> 00:23:51,743
that they have for new guests.

334
00:23:51,911 --> 00:23:54,579
Mom, I can't hear you.
Oh, thanks.

335
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:58,917
You know,
it's like an introductory game.

336
00:23:59,043 --> 00:24:00,919
I'll bet 200.

337
00:24:03,672 --> 00:24:05,256
See it.

338
00:24:13,224 --> 00:24:16,226
- See it.
- Well, I'm out.

339
00:24:19,230 --> 00:24:22,065
See the 200 and...
Oh, God...

340
00:24:23,984 --> 00:24:25,568
...raise a hundred.

341
00:24:26,445 --> 00:24:28,613
Too rich for my blood.

342
00:24:28,781 --> 00:24:30,615
See your hundred.

343
00:24:36,121 --> 00:24:39,624
Raise you... a thousand.

344
00:24:43,295 --> 00:24:45,463
This is out of control.

345
00:24:47,383 --> 00:24:48,550
I'm out.

346
00:24:49,802 --> 00:24:51,719
See the thousand.

347
00:24:54,974 --> 00:24:57,976
- We're it, huh?
- Just us chickens.

348
00:25:00,896 --> 00:25:03,189
Both.

349
00:25:03,315 --> 00:25:04,816
Aces over eights.

350
00:25:05,526 --> 00:25:08,444
- Shit!
- Excellent!

351
00:25:08,571 --> 00:25:09,904
This is terrific.

352
00:25:11,115 --> 00:25:14,617
You played that hand like,
"Forget about it," huh?

353
00:25:15,327 --> 00:25:17,328
Thanks. I'm in a regular game
in the city.

354
00:25:17,454 --> 00:25:20,748
Really? You got to tell me that.

355
00:25:26,505 --> 00:25:29,007
I'll call you
right before the ceremony.

356
00:25:29,133 --> 00:25:32,176
Like 10:30 your time.

357
00:25:32,344 --> 00:25:33,886
Of course I'm excited.
What do you think?

358
00:25:43,689 --> 00:25:46,774
(Elvis impersonator) ♪ Well, bright
light city gonna set my soul

359
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:49,736
♪ Gonna set my soul on fire

360
00:25:49,862 --> 00:25:52,739
- ♪ I got a whole lot of money...
- Could you shut the fuck up?

361
00:25:52,865 --> 00:25:56,159
Tony, there's absolutely no need
for that type of language here.

362
00:25:57,536 --> 00:25:59,579
All right. Oh...

363
00:26:00,914 --> 00:26:03,499
I raise... 500.

364
00:26:06,712 --> 00:26:08,171
I fold.

365
00:26:09,465 --> 00:26:12,717
Well, baby, the King must fold.

366
00:26:15,262 --> 00:26:17,889
I'll see the 500...

367
00:26:18,599 --> 00:26:19,891
...and I'll raise 2,000.

368
00:26:20,017 --> 00:26:24,979
- You must have tremendous confidence.
- I have tremendous confidence.

369
00:26:26,565 --> 00:26:28,107
Say "good night," Gracie.

370
00:26:29,401 --> 00:26:31,486
A little confidence
ain't going to get it, kid.

371
00:26:33,364 --> 00:26:37,200
I see the 2,500
and raise you three grand.

372
00:26:38,410 --> 00:26:39,911
I think you got nothin'.

373
00:26:40,871 --> 00:26:43,164
That's your constitutional right.

374
00:26:43,290 --> 00:26:46,376
OK. That's the kind of game
we're going to play...

375
00:26:48,754 --> 00:26:50,505
That's five to me...

376
00:26:54,009 --> 00:26:55,760
...and...

377
00:26:57,888 --> 00:26:58,930
I raise you 8,000.

378
00:27:00,432 --> 00:27:02,308
(man) Tommy, I thought
we were playing for fun.

379
00:27:02,434 --> 00:27:04,268
This is fun.

380
00:27:04,395 --> 00:27:07,146
♪ Wise men say

381
00:27:07,272 --> 00:27:09,440
♪ Only fools rush in

382
00:27:09,566 --> 00:27:11,776
Eddie, please.

383
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:16,114
We may have to institute
a ban on singing here.

384
00:27:16,281 --> 00:27:19,450
I'll see the eight grand.
I'll raise you ten.

385
00:27:21,286 --> 00:27:23,996
Can I borrow 21 grand, please?

386
00:27:25,249 --> 00:27:27,166
Twenty-one grand?

387
00:27:29,253 --> 00:27:32,171
You know you can buy
a friggin' Volvo for 21 grand? Turbo?

388
00:27:34,216 --> 00:27:35,633
I know what I'm doin'.

389
00:27:38,637 --> 00:27:42,849
- You got some guts, kid.
- It's not guts. It's realism.

390
00:27:44,476 --> 00:27:46,978
(chatter)

391
00:27:56,071 --> 00:27:57,989
There's 83 grand in there.

392
00:28:02,661 --> 00:28:03,870
Jackson, what's the word?

393
00:28:07,666 --> 00:28:09,584
I'll see it...

394
00:28:11,962 --> 00:28:13,796
...and I'll raise you ten.

395
00:28:13,922 --> 00:28:15,923
25,000 more, please.

396
00:28:17,384 --> 00:28:19,761
This kid's got some set of balls.
Am I right?

397
00:28:21,555 --> 00:28:23,556
My hat's off to you, kid.

398
00:28:23,682 --> 00:28:26,184
My shirt too, probably,
the way you play.

399
00:28:35,027 --> 00:28:36,152
To you.

400
00:28:40,032 --> 00:28:43,451
Tick-tock, tick-tock, tick-tock.

401
00:28:46,163 --> 00:28:48,539
Well, might as well
go down in flames.

402
00:28:54,838 --> 00:28:56,339
What do you got?

403
00:28:57,466 --> 00:29:01,219
Sorry, man.
Straight flush to the jack.

404
00:29:06,350 --> 00:29:09,602
That's... That's one for the books.

405
00:29:11,396 --> 00:29:12,772
(sighs)

406
00:29:12,898 --> 00:29:19,612
To the queen.

407
00:29:20,906 --> 00:29:22,240
(gasping)

408
00:29:22,407 --> 00:29:24,909
That's a tough break.

409
00:29:26,703 --> 00:29:28,830
Would you like a fruit plate?

410
00:29:28,956 --> 00:29:30,456
(woman on PA, indistinct)

411
00:29:36,338 --> 00:29:39,257
I'm not assessing any blame here.

412
00:29:41,176 --> 00:29:45,096
But the reality is that you're
in a tremendous amount of trouble.

413
00:29:46,098 --> 00:29:48,307
- If I go to a loan shark...
- Loan shark?

414
00:29:48,433 --> 00:29:50,852
What loan shark's
going to give you 65,000?

415
00:29:50,978 --> 00:29:52,812
If you haven't got it,
there's no way you can pay it back.

416
00:29:52,938 --> 00:29:54,605
If you can, give it to me.

417
00:29:57,359 --> 00:30:00,444
- I can't.
- Nonpayment of debts.

418
00:30:00,571 --> 00:30:02,864
That's extremely serious everywhere.

419
00:30:02,990 --> 00:30:05,950
I mean, among people. Among countries,
governments... They don't give a shit.

420
00:30:06,076 --> 00:30:08,160
Am I right? They stiff everybody.

421
00:30:09,538 --> 00:30:13,332
But... (clears throat)
...individuals...

422
00:30:15,335 --> 00:30:18,796
They are expected to pay debts.

423
00:30:19,631 --> 00:30:21,299
Especially gambling debts.

424
00:30:22,509 --> 00:30:25,845
That's the essence of gambling.

425
00:30:25,971 --> 00:30:27,388
You risk something.

426
00:30:28,891 --> 00:30:31,642
If you put up money
you haven't got and can't get...

427
00:30:33,353 --> 00:30:35,354
That's the lowest.

428
00:30:39,484 --> 00:30:40,985
People...

429
00:30:41,111 --> 00:30:44,405
People can get badly injured.

430
00:30:44,531 --> 00:30:46,657
Jack, I'm talking physically.

431
00:30:48,243 --> 00:30:51,787
Maybe we could work out something
over a period of a couple years.

432
00:30:51,914 --> 00:30:55,708
Hey, what do you think?
You're buying a damn washer and dryer?

433
00:30:55,834 --> 00:30:58,669
You owe Tommy Korman $65,000,
you understand?

434
00:30:58,837 --> 00:31:01,756
Look, I'll rack my brain.

435
00:31:01,882 --> 00:31:04,967
It's all right. I already racked mine.

436
00:31:05,093 --> 00:31:07,970
- Do you have a solution?
- I do.

437
00:31:15,187 --> 00:31:16,938
I want...

438
00:31:21,109 --> 00:31:23,027
...your girlfriend for the weekend.

439
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:27,615
Betsy?
How do you know Betsy?

440
00:31:27,741 --> 00:31:30,284
I don't... I don't know Betsy.

441
00:31:30,410 --> 00:31:35,081
I don't know her.
I saw her over there in the lobby.

442
00:31:36,625 --> 00:31:40,002
See, my wife Donna...
May she rest in peace...

443
00:31:40,128 --> 00:31:43,255
They look identical.
I mean, they could be twins.

444
00:31:43,382 --> 00:31:46,801
Now, I'm willing
to wipe out the 65 bills...

445
00:31:47,928 --> 00:31:50,513
...if you let me
spend the weekend with her.

446
00:31:51,598 --> 00:31:54,016
We're getting married tonight.

447
00:31:54,142 --> 00:31:58,354
No, no, no, not tonight.
After the weekend.

448
00:32:00,565 --> 00:32:04,151
And, Jack,
I'll be a perfect gentleman.

449
00:32:05,278 --> 00:32:08,614
I just want company.

450
00:32:10,742 --> 00:32:13,077
She won't agree to this.

451
00:32:13,245 --> 00:32:15,788
If she loves you,
she'll agree to this.

452
00:32:17,708 --> 00:32:21,836
(up-tempo music over PA)

453
00:32:21,962 --> 00:32:23,546
(woman on PA) May I have
your attention, please.

454
00:32:23,672 --> 00:32:24,672
Hi!

455
00:32:24,798 --> 00:32:27,425
Bally's Casino Resort
is pleased to announce...

456
00:32:27,592 --> 00:32:30,052
another $12,000 winner...

457
00:32:30,178 --> 00:32:35,099
on one of Bally's
hot 97 percent dollar slot machines.

458
00:32:35,225 --> 00:32:37,518
Congratulations to the winner.

459
00:32:52,284 --> 00:32:53,451
What happened?

460
00:32:56,329 --> 00:32:57,788
We, uh...

461
00:32:59,624 --> 00:33:02,334
We have to have a serious talk.

462
00:33:04,504 --> 00:33:05,504
(crowd cheering)

463
00:33:05,630 --> 00:33:08,215
- (Betsy) Are you out of your mind?
- I said you wouldn't do it.

464
00:33:08,341 --> 00:33:10,301
- Is that what you really said?
- Of course. What do you think?

465
00:33:10,469 --> 00:33:14,180
And he actually said, "If she
spends the weekend with me,

466
00:33:14,306 --> 00:33:16,057
you owe me nothing?"

467
00:33:16,183 --> 00:33:18,434
- Yes.
- I am so nauseous.

468
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:20,311
You don't think
this is totally killing me?

469
00:33:20,479 --> 00:33:23,606
You know, I had this feeling when you
left, then I talked myself out of it.

470
00:33:23,732 --> 00:33:28,152
- Something about this is not right.
- Listen. Just forget I mentioned it.

471
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:30,362
- There's options.
- Like what?

472
00:33:30,489 --> 00:33:32,698
Neither of us has any money.

473
00:33:32,824 --> 00:33:35,826
God, Jack! What did he say?

474
00:33:35,952 --> 00:33:38,120
He wants me to walk around
in her clothes?

475
00:33:39,790 --> 00:33:43,667
- He wasn't that specific.
- How could you put me in this position?

476
00:33:43,794 --> 00:33:47,838
What do you think? I knew it was coming?
I wanted this to happen?

477
00:33:47,964 --> 00:33:50,758
- I was completely blindsided.
- I still don't understand this.

478
00:33:50,884 --> 00:33:54,512
You went in there with $500.
We had this whole discussion.

479
00:33:54,638 --> 00:33:57,056
I had a straight flush!

480
00:33:57,182 --> 00:34:01,519
Do you know what a straight flush is?
It's, like, unbeatable.

481
00:34:01,645 --> 00:34:04,021
"Like unbeatable" is not "unbeatable."

482
00:34:04,147 --> 00:34:06,190
Hey, I know that now, OK?

483
00:34:06,358 --> 00:34:09,568
Don't yell at me! I hate this place!

484
00:34:09,694 --> 00:34:11,695
I won't sleep with him,
no matter who he is.

485
00:34:11,822 --> 00:34:14,406
Are you crazy? Of course not.
That's not even a consideration.

