596
00:40:50,970 --> 00:40:53,639
I got a place in Kauai.

597
00:40:53,765 --> 00:40:56,350
It's right on the beach.
It'll knock your socks off.

598
00:40:57,519 --> 00:41:02,064
Chris'll be there, his wife, baby.
Be a real family time.

599
00:41:02,941 --> 00:41:03,941
(coughing)

600
00:41:08,738 --> 00:41:10,864
(woman) Twenty. Black even.

601
00:41:15,203 --> 00:41:16,787
Place your bets.

602
00:41:16,913 --> 00:41:18,789
Hi, old-timer.
Are you feeling lucky?

603
00:41:18,957 --> 00:41:20,707
Actually, I'm not.

604
00:41:21,626 --> 00:41:23,293
(woman on PA)

605
00:41:37,392 --> 00:41:39,184
- Betsy!
- Hi.

606
00:41:39,310 --> 00:41:41,520
- So what's the story?
- I have to pack.

607
00:41:41,646 --> 00:41:44,356
We can leave!
What did you work out?

608
00:41:45,358 --> 00:41:47,818
He's taking me to Hawaii.

609
00:41:47,986 --> 00:41:50,487
- It's only for a few days.
- Come on.

610
00:41:50,655 --> 00:41:53,991
You're so, like, blithe about this all
of a sudden, like you don't give a damn!

611
00:41:54,117 --> 00:41:58,036
Of course I give a damn, but this
was not my idea. Poker was not my idea.

612
00:41:58,162 --> 00:42:00,539
Would you please
stop crucifying me with this?

613
00:42:00,665 --> 00:42:01,748
Have you seen my bag?

614
00:42:01,874 --> 00:42:03,584
He's going to jump all over you
the second he gets there.

615
00:42:03,710 --> 00:42:05,335
And I'll let him?
Give me a little credit.

616
00:42:05,461 --> 00:42:07,713
He'll overcome you.
What happens if you start screaming?

617
00:42:07,839 --> 00:42:09,840
It's like a jungle over there!

618
00:42:09,966 --> 00:42:13,844
He probably has servants and bodyguards,
and believe me, they will drug you!

619
00:42:14,012 --> 00:42:17,681
His son is going to be there.
His granddaughter Tiffany will be there.

620
00:42:17,849 --> 00:42:20,350
She knows the kid's name already.

621
00:42:23,187 --> 00:42:24,563
OK.

622
00:42:26,190 --> 00:42:28,108
- Marry me tonight.
- No.

623
00:42:28,234 --> 00:42:30,527
- No? Why not?
- Because I don't believe you.

624
00:42:30,695 --> 00:42:34,364
If you really wanted to marry me,
you would've done it this afternoon.

625
00:42:34,532 --> 00:42:35,907
Yes, this is the Ali Baba Suite.

626
00:42:36,034 --> 00:42:38,577
I have some bags
that have to be brought down.

627
00:42:40,288 --> 00:42:42,164
Yes, thank you.

628
00:42:42,290 --> 00:42:44,041
You were looking
for a way to get out of this.

629
00:42:44,208 --> 00:42:46,251
I mean, you don't have to be Freud
to figure that one out.

630
00:42:46,377 --> 00:42:48,545
I was not looking!

631
00:42:50,048 --> 00:42:53,925
Listen... You'll be back Monday?

632
00:42:54,052 --> 00:42:55,886
I don't know.
Probably Tuesday or Wednesday.

633
00:42:56,012 --> 00:42:58,055
Tuesday or Wednesday!
That's almost a week!

634
00:42:58,222 --> 00:43:02,225
What, you expect us to fly
back and forth to Hawaii in two days?

635
00:43:02,352 --> 00:43:04,269
"Us"? Already it's "us."

636
00:43:04,395 --> 00:43:07,022
Don't be infantile!
I'm trying to make the best of this!

637
00:43:07,148 --> 00:43:09,066
Well, you're doing great!

638
00:43:09,233 --> 00:43:11,401
(♪ Billy Joel: All Shook Up)

639
00:43:20,620 --> 00:43:22,913
Hey, Mr. Straight Flush.
We got a free seat.

640
00:43:23,039 --> 00:43:26,249
- Where's Tommy?
- He just left for Hawaii.

641
00:43:26,376 --> 00:43:28,293
What are you talking about, just left?

642
00:43:28,961 --> 00:43:30,837
The phone rang.
They said the car was ready.

643
00:43:30,963 --> 00:43:32,673
What? He left already?

644
00:43:46,270 --> 00:43:48,188
I don't know about this.

645
00:43:51,275 --> 00:43:54,236
See, you gotta
think about it like this:

646
00:43:55,697 --> 00:43:58,782
You're doing this
to get Jack off the hook.

647
00:43:58,950 --> 00:44:02,869
And your going away makes him realize
how nuts he is about you.

648
00:44:02,995 --> 00:44:06,373
And he appreciates you double
when you come back.

649
00:44:06,499 --> 00:44:08,375
(slot machines ringing)

650
00:44:11,129 --> 00:44:14,506
He agreed to this,
so he's got to be... what?

651
00:44:14,632 --> 00:44:16,466
- Ambivalent?
- Yeah. Right.

652
00:44:21,681 --> 00:44:24,975
Stop! No!

653
00:44:25,476 --> 00:44:26,810
(car horns honking)

654
00:44:30,815 --> 00:44:33,108
(man on TV) Much of the guesswork
is removed from poker

655
00:44:33,234 --> 00:44:37,154
with any of the following hands:
A full house, four of a kind,

656
00:44:37,321 --> 00:44:38,947
or the emperor of all hands:

657
00:44:39,073 --> 00:44:41,825
The invincible,
unbeatable straight flush.

658
00:44:43,244 --> 00:44:45,328
(♪ Billy Joel: Heartbreak Hotel)

659
00:44:45,496 --> 00:44:47,372
(chattering)

660
00:44:57,091 --> 00:44:58,550
(coins dropping)

661
00:45:05,808 --> 00:45:08,602
I have to get out of here.

662
00:45:18,613 --> 00:45:20,489
(♪ Willie Nelson: Blue Hawaii)

663
00:45:52,897 --> 00:45:54,898
(Betsy) This is amazing.

664
00:45:55,066 --> 00:45:57,400
(Tommy) Ah... Thank you.
I like it.

665
00:45:57,527 --> 00:46:00,570
It's a place
for quiet reflection. Niko...

666
00:46:01,197 --> 00:46:03,281
(speaking Hawaiian)

667
00:46:05,535 --> 00:46:08,787
See, I said to him,
"How's the weather?" in Hawaiian...

668
00:46:08,913 --> 00:46:13,583
and then he said,
"Great. It's in the 80s. Low humidity."

669
00:46:13,751 --> 00:46:17,254
- He doesn't speak English?
- Fluently, thank you.

670
00:46:17,380 --> 00:46:19,714
Welcome to Hawaii.

671
00:46:19,841 --> 00:46:21,925
You know, Mr. Korman
is like a god over here.

672
00:46:22,051 --> 00:46:24,594
Hey, Niko, please.
You're really embarrassing me here.

673
00:46:24,720 --> 00:46:26,596
(windchimes clinking)

674
00:46:34,897 --> 00:46:36,815
I don't believe this.

675
00:46:40,027 --> 00:46:44,030
This... This'll be your room.

676
00:46:44,156 --> 00:46:47,951
God, this is breathtaking.

677
00:46:48,077 --> 00:46:51,830
I... (clears throat)
I rebuilt it about a year ago.

678
00:46:54,125 --> 00:46:55,625
(speaks Hawaiian)

679
00:46:57,128 --> 00:46:59,296
My home by the sea.

680
00:46:59,463 --> 00:47:01,798
You can probably
knock off the Hawaiian now.

681
00:47:01,924 --> 00:47:02,924
Oh?

682
00:47:03,050 --> 00:47:06,595
- I've impressed you enough, then?
- More than enough.

683
00:47:07,471 --> 00:47:10,348
God. I've been to the Caribbean...

684
00:47:10,474 --> 00:47:13,560
The Caribbean? You know who goes
to the Caribbean? Dentists.

685
00:47:13,686 --> 00:47:16,104
That's who goes to the Caribbean.

686
00:47:16,230 --> 00:47:19,482
- It's so beautiful.
- Yeah.

687
00:47:21,986 --> 00:47:23,403
You know, we have a...

688
00:47:24,530 --> 00:47:28,158
We have a name
for this time of day here.

689
00:47:28,326 --> 00:47:30,035
Waka-waka?

690
00:47:30,411 --> 00:47:32,162
It's close.

691
00:47:32,330 --> 00:47:34,080
(speaks Hawaiian)

692
00:47:36,542 --> 00:47:38,001
Time of enchantment.

693
00:47:40,004 --> 00:47:41,379
What did I tell you?

694
00:47:44,300 --> 00:47:47,677
- You got this in the mail?
- Under my door at home.

695
00:47:50,389 --> 00:47:52,682
Mr. Tomashefsky, it's a joke!

696
00:47:52,808 --> 00:47:55,018
I mean, it's not even close.

697
00:47:55,144 --> 00:47:59,731
