00:51:09,213 --> 00:51:13,424
I mean, for one thing,
you're a lot smarter than she was.

732
00:51:13,551 --> 00:51:15,844
God forgive me for saying that.

733
00:51:15,970 --> 00:51:17,554
Look. I've got to say
something else too.

734
00:51:17,721 --> 00:51:19,472
You're pissin' your life away

735
00:51:19,598 --> 00:51:21,724
on a guy that can't pull the trigger
on marrying you.

736
00:51:21,892 --> 00:51:24,144
We were gonna get married.

737
00:51:24,270 --> 00:51:27,230
With me, I'd have gone right from the
airport to the chapel to marry you.

738
00:51:27,398 --> 00:51:29,274
- What did he do?
- You have to understand Jack.

739
00:51:29,400 --> 00:51:32,152
This man, he decided to play poker.
That's what this man did.

740
00:51:32,278 --> 00:51:34,612
- He had a very strange mother.
- He played poker.

741
00:51:34,738 --> 00:51:36,531
He's a...

742
00:51:37,575 --> 00:51:40,410
He's a great... a great guy, I'm sure.

743
00:51:40,578 --> 00:51:42,412
I'm just sayin'...

744
00:51:43,455 --> 00:51:46,082
I'm just sayin' think about it
before you marry him.

745
00:51:46,250 --> 00:51:48,626
- Just...
- (man) Hey, Dad! Dad!

746
00:51:48,752 --> 00:51:52,422
- There are the kids.
- How far is Mount Kilauea from here?

747
00:51:52,548 --> 00:51:55,049
- It's on the other island. Why?
- (baby crying)

748
00:51:55,759 --> 00:51:57,302
We heard it's erupting.

749
00:51:58,387 --> 00:52:00,763
We gotta go. We gotta go.

750
00:52:00,931 --> 00:52:02,348
Listen.

751
00:52:03,851 --> 00:52:06,477
Did I upset you?
Because if I did, I...

752
00:52:06,604 --> 00:52:08,897
No. I mean, you touched a nerve.

753
00:52:09,023 --> 00:52:12,400
Look. It's just,
Jack is very complicated.

754
00:52:13,277 --> 00:52:14,777
Yeah.

755
00:52:14,945 --> 00:52:18,156
You see, I've known guys
like him my whole life.

756
00:52:18,282 --> 00:52:20,450
Decent, good guys.
They're real good guys.

757
00:52:20,618 --> 00:52:23,828
But they cause a lot of heartache.

758
00:52:25,664 --> 00:52:27,624
I don't think you deserve that.

759
00:52:28,626 --> 00:52:30,418
I think you deserve a lot better.

760
00:52:33,505 --> 00:52:35,381
(man on TV) Winds out of the northwest
at seven miles per hour.

761
00:52:35,507 --> 00:52:37,508
It's currently cloudy
with a chance of...

762
00:52:42,765 --> 00:52:47,060
(woman 1) Take a look, everybody.
The Oleg Cassini men's...

763
00:52:47,186 --> 00:52:49,229
(woman 2) Mother Nature
put on a show yesterday...

764
00:52:49,355 --> 00:52:51,397
as Hawaii's Mount Kilauea erupted.

765
00:52:51,523 --> 00:52:53,691
We have a report from Connie Wong.

766
00:52:56,195 --> 00:52:58,905
Mount Kilauea,
dormant for the past eight years...

767
00:52:59,031 --> 00:53:01,991
erupted last night
with spectacular force.

768
00:53:02,159 --> 00:53:05,662
Rivers of fire streamed down from
the volcano beginning around midnight,

769
00:53:05,788 --> 00:53:07,997
and word spread quickly
throughout the islands.

770
00:53:08,165 --> 00:53:09,707
Natives and tourists alike

771
00:53:09,833 --> 00:53:11,834
thronged to the base of Mount Kilauea

772
00:53:11,961 --> 00:53:15,672
to watch nature's fury unleashed...
with awe-inspiring force.

773
00:53:15,839 --> 00:53:20,343
Government officials stress no one was
in immediate danger from the eruption.

774
00:53:20,469 --> 00:53:23,888
If I take the 7:00pm,
I get to Milwaukee when?

775
00:53:24,014 --> 00:53:27,350
- 8:35.
- 8:35. And that's Central Time?

776
00:53:27,518 --> 00:53:29,143
Yes, sir.

777
00:53:29,270 --> 00:53:32,689
Now, would it be any cheaper
if I stop in Nashville?

778
00:53:32,815 --> 00:53:35,275
- Same price, sir.
- I hold an AAdvantage card.

779
00:53:35,401 --> 00:53:37,443
That won't make any difference
in the price.

780
00:53:37,569 --> 00:53:39,821
Sir, there seems
to be a very long line.

781
00:53:41,532 --> 00:53:45,285
- Tell me again about the Super Saver.
- There are several restrictions.

782
00:53:45,411 --> 00:53:47,704
What's this guy doing?
Around the world in 80 days?

783
00:53:47,871 --> 00:53:49,580
- Lighten up.
- You lighten up.

784
00:53:49,707 --> 00:53:52,208
You can only fly on a Tuesday,
Wednesday, Thursday...

785
00:53:52,334 --> 00:53:55,753
That's it. Look. Look.
I've got a major problem.

786
00:53:55,879 --> 00:53:58,715
OK? My fiancée was kidnapped
and taken to Hawaii.

787
00:53:58,882 --> 00:54:00,925
I've got to get there now.

788
00:54:01,051 --> 00:54:03,720
Well, I'm trying to make arrangements
to get to Milwaukee...

789
00:54:03,846 --> 00:54:06,556
for my nephew Douglas's wedding
on the 21st.

790
00:54:07,725 --> 00:54:09,559
You're not even flying today?

791
00:54:09,727 --> 00:54:11,728
No. Consumer Reports said

792
00:54:11,895 --> 00:54:14,772
if you make your travel arrangements
two weeks in advance at...

793
00:54:14,898 --> 00:54:18,443
You see this line?
We're all flying today.

794
00:54:18,569 --> 00:54:20,987
- Sir, if you don't get back in line...
- Then what?

795
00:54:21,113 --> 00:54:23,740
I'll be arrested? Put in airport jail?

796
00:54:23,866 --> 00:54:27,994
Just get your ticket and move on.
Get your goddamn ticket and move on!

797
00:54:28,120 --> 00:54:29,579
(man) Yeah!

798
00:54:38,464 --> 00:54:41,591
(Betsy) The whole point of the game
was me? Getting me here?

799
00:54:42,843 --> 00:54:46,054
(Tommy) All right.
Why keep it a secret any longer?

800
00:54:46,930 --> 00:54:48,306
My heart's on my sleeve.

801
00:54:50,559 --> 00:54:53,644
From the minute I saw you
in that lobby, I knew...

802
00:54:53,771 --> 00:54:56,773
- So you sort of lied to me.
- How's that?

803
00:54:56,940 --> 00:54:59,692
I understood that this was like
a settlement of the game,

804
00:54:59,818 --> 00:55:01,944
when, in fact, it was
the whole reason for the game.

805
00:55:02,071 --> 00:55:04,781
Yeah. So? Aren't you flattered?

806
00:55:04,907 --> 00:55:07,116
You told me
the game was legitimate.

807
00:55:07,284 --> 00:55:09,619
The game was legitimate.

808
00:55:09,787 --> 00:55:11,954
But, I mean,
I play cards professionally,

809
00:55:12,081 --> 00:55:14,457
and no amateur's gonna beat me.

810
00:55:14,625 --> 00:55:16,959
That's what I had to do to get you.

811
00:55:17,086 --> 00:55:21,464
If I was a medieval knight,
I'd have jostled for you.

812
00:55:21,590 --> 00:55:23,424
Jousted. That's jousted.

813
00:55:23,550 --> 00:55:25,259
Jousted. Whatever the hell they did.

814
00:55:25,386 --> 00:55:28,346
Look, if that is
your preoccupation here...

815
00:55:28,472 --> 00:55:31,557
If you want to leave tomorrow

816
00:55:31,683 --> 00:55:34,602
instead of Wednesday,
believe me, I understand.

817
00:55:34,728 --> 00:55:37,105
I'll call and make reservations.

818
00:55:37,231 --> 00:55:40,149
- No.
- "No?" No calls?

819
00:55:40,275 --> 00:55:42,902
No. No, I'm having a wonderful time.

820
00:55:43,028 --> 00:55:44,904
It's just, you know, this is...

821
00:55:45,030 --> 00:55:48,658
It's just a little overwhelming
to be pursued like this.

822
00:55:48,826 --> 00:55:50,034
Well, no one ever...

823
00:55:50,869 --> 00:55:54,288
...ever was as crazy
about you as I am.

824
00:55:55,791 --> 00:55:58,126
I mean, it's up there with...

825
00:55:58,252 --> 00:56:02,922
...Romeo and Juliet,
George and Gracie... All the big ones.

826
00:56:03,924 --> 00:56:05,299
(sighs)

827
00:56:05,426 --> 00:56:07,427
I'll take care of you forever.

828
00:56:07,553 --> 00:56:09,929
I would throw myself
in front of a train for you.

829
00:56:17,604 --> 00:56:19,772
Just stop me at any time.

830
00:56:30,409 --> 00:56:33,703
Was that wrong?
It didn't feel wrong to me.

831
00:56:35,789 --> 00:56:39,959
I don't know.

832
00:56:42,212 --> 00:56:44,255
It's OK, honey.
Let me see here.

833
00:56:44,381 --> 00:56:46,883
- What are you doing?
- She's got a great spitball.

834
00:56:47,050 --> 00:56:50,219
- (telephone ringing)
- That's a tremendous natural athlete.

835
00:56:50,345 --> 00:56:51,846
- Yeah?
- (Niko) Telephone, Mr. K.

836
00:56:51,972 --> 00:56:53,848
- Do you want to hold her?
- Yes.

837
00:56:53,974 --> 00:56:55,850
- Can I hold you?
- Yes.

838
00:56:55,976 --> 00:56:59,061
Oh, hey. That's great
how she goes to you like that.

839
00:56:59,229 --> 00:57:01,606
I can't believe it. She doesn't
go to people like that.

840
00:57:01,732 --> 00:57:02,982
Gimme.

841
00:57:09,072 --> 00:57:10,072
What's the story?

842
00:57:10,199 --> 00:57:13,910
Bad news.
He's on the morning flight in.

843
00:57:15,078 --> 00:57:17,663
I'm surprised
and I'm not surprised.

844
00:57:18,749 --> 00:57:23,878
Look. All right. We gotta keep him
away from here for at least a day.

845
00:57:24,546 --> 00:57:26,130
How 'bout a nice hit-and-run?

846
00:57:28,091 --> 00:57:29,759
Look, no violence.

847
00:57:29,885 --> 00:57:32,345
Unless it's absolutely
necessary, all right?

848
00:57:32,471 --> 00:57:35,515
(Tommy) Just stall,
and get the chief. Get Mahi.

849
00:57:35,641 --> 00:57:37,433
Just take care of it.

850
00:57:38,769 --> 00:57:42,063
Look, I'm getting very close
with her, you know?

851
00:57:42,189 --> 00:57:45,107
And if he shows up over here,
it's over, and...

852
00:57:45,234 --> 00:57:47,944
- (crunching sounds)
- Are you goddamn eating again?

853
00:57:49,613 --> 00:57:51,739
No, I swear, I'm not eatin'.

854
00:57:58,747 --> 00:58:00,373
He checked out Sunday?

855
00:58:00,499 --> 00:58:02,500
(man) At 8:07.

856
00:58:02,626 --> 00:58:04,502
Can I help you
with any future reservations?

857
00:58:04,628 --> 00:58:06,671
- No, thank you.
- Thank you for calling Bally's.

858
00:58:19,476 --> 00:58:22,061
Come on, come on, come on.

859
00:58:23,146 --> 00:58:24,689
(Jack on machine)
Hi, this is Jack Singer.

860
00:58:24,815 --> 00:58:26,440
Sorry I can't take your call now,

861
00:58:26,567 --> 00:58:31,153
but if you'd leave your name
and number, I'll get right back to you.

862
00:58:33,282 --> 00:58:34,448
Shit!

863
00:58:52,175 --> 00:58:54,677
Hey, Mahi,
will you pay some attention?

864
00:58:56,013 --> 00:58:57,888
This guy, Jack Singer's
six-one, about 180.

865
00:58:58,015 --> 00:58:59,390
He's coming out of that terminal.

866
00:58:59,516 --> 00:59:01,225
Keep him away from Tommy's all right?

867
00:59:01,351 --> 00:59:04,228
I don't care where you take him.
Just keep him away from Tommy's.

868
00:59:04,354 --> 00:59:06,355
- Sure.
- All right, Mahi.

869
00:59:08,775 --> 00:59:10,776
(woman on PA)

870
00:59:14,906 --> 00:59:17,533
Hey, brother, you like ride?

871
00:59:17,701 --> 00:59:20,369
Yeah, I need a ride,
but I don't know where yet.

872
00:59:20,495 --> 00:59:21,912
- I take your bag.
- Thanks.

873
00:59:22,039 --> 00:59:24,206
My name Mahi.
Mahi Mahi.

874
00:59:24,333 --> 00:59:26,876
- Like the fish?
- Yeah. My father was a fisherman.

875
00:59:27,002 --> 00:59:29,837
My father left home when I was five.
That's why I'm named Jack.

876
00:59:30,005 --> 00:59:32,506
As in "Jack, tell your mother
I'm going to get the paper."

877
00:59:32,633 --> 00:59:35,343
- I gotta make a couple calls.
- Hey, Jack, Jack.

878
00:59:35,469 --> 00:59:37,386
Where you like go?
Tell me. I take you anywhere.

879
00:59:37,554 --> 00:59:41,557
Do you have any idea where a guy
named Tommy Korman lives?

880
00:59:41,683 --> 00:59:44,310
Sure. Everybody know that.

881
00:59:44,436 --> 00:59:45,728
You're kidding?

882
00:59:45,896 --> 00:59:49,398
- No, it's a small island.
- This is great.

883
00:59:50,317 --> 00:59:52,318
Thought I was going to have
to go through a whole number.

884
00:59:52,444 --> 00:59:54,153
- Cab's over here.
- All right.

885
00:59:54,279 --> 00:59:55,655
Welcome to Kauai.

886
01:00:01,745 --> 01:00:02,828
You like this, Jack?

887
01:00:02,954 --> 01:00:06,624
Beautiful, huh? So romantic.

888
01:00:06,750 --> 01:00:09,377
The women, when they come here,
oh, they get crazy.

889
01:00:09,503 --> 01:00:11,504
They like "freaky-freaky"
all night long.

890
01:00:11,630 --> 01:00:13,589
That's really great news.
We almost there?

891
01:00:13,715 --> 01:00:16,634
Yeah. Right up here
about a mile and a half.

892
01:00:35,112 --> 01:00:38,572
This can't be it.
Tommy Korman lives here?

893
01:00:38,699 --> 01:00:40,032
Korman?

894
01:00:40,158 --> 01:00:42,702
I thought you said "Orman."
You know, Chief Orman.

895
01:00:42,828 --> 01:00:44,704
I didn't say Chief Orman.

896
01:00:44,830 --> 01:00:47,957
I said Tommy Korman,
loud and clear. Come on!

897
01:00:48,083 --> 01:00:51,711
I fly for two goddamn days,
I haven't slept, I can barely walk!

898
01:00:53,839 --> 01:00:55,756
(speaking Hawaiian)

899
01:01:00,804 --> 01:01:04,140
That goes double for me, chief.
There was a little mix-up here.

900
01:01:04,266 --> 01:01:06,851
(speaking Hawaiian)

901
01:01:09,646 --> 01:01:11,230
(repeats Hawaiian word)

902
01:01:11,356 --> 01:01:12,398
Listen, Mahi.

903
01:01:12,524 --> 01:01:14,692
I don't have time
for this horseshit!

904
01:01:15,777 --> 01:01:18,988
Hey, Jack, no make insult
for the chief, OK?

905
01:01:19,114 --> 01:01:21,073
This man get plenty influence
in this place.

906
01:01:21,199 --> 01:01:23,534
"Influence"?
He lives in a shack!

907
01:01:25,120 --> 01:01:27,496
He's a man of great simplicity.

908
01:01:28,665 --> 01:01:31,751
Come on. You spend
ten minutes with the guy, OK?

909
01:01:31,877 --> 01:01:35,421
If you don't do that, the word
gonna get around Kauai so fast.

910
01:01:35,547 --> 01:01:38,799
Next thing you know,
ain't nobody gonna help you, brother.

911
01:01:43,597 --> 01:01:46,599
- Parakeet brandy.
- Are you serious?

912
01:01:51,354 --> 01:01:52,480
(sighs)

913
01:01:53,356 --> 01:01:56,150
(speaks Hawaiian)

914
01:01:56,693 --> 01:01:57,902
(gasps, gags)

915
01:01:59,905 --> 01:02:02,865
- You are from mainland?
- That's right.

916
01:02:03,992 --> 01:02:06,035
Do you find Chief Orman attractive?

917
01:02:10,999 --> 01:02:13,709
Uh... You're
a striking-looking figure.

918
01:02:13,835 --> 01:02:16,170
If by "attractive"...

919
01:02:16,296 --> 01:02:17,630
(Mahi) Hey, chief.

920
01:02:17,756 --> 01:02:20,716
He looking for a man
named Tommy Korman.

921
01:02:20,884 --> 01:02:22,384
If you know where he is...

922
01:02:22,552 --> 01:02:25,346
Have you seen the musical
Grand Hotel?

923
01:02:27,432 --> 01:02:29,850
I... I don't go
to the theater that often.

924
01:02:29,976 --> 01:02:32,394
Do you know if it
will come to Kauai?

925
01:02:33,939 --> 01:02:36,482
I don't, really, but I'll
ask around when I get back.

926
01:02:36,608 --> 01:02:38,317
Now, could you tell me...

927
01:02:38,443 --> 01:02:40,402
Did you hear me before
about Tommy Korman?

928
01:02:42,364 --> 01:02:46,075
Chief Orman favorite is,
of course, South Pacific.

929
01:02:48,912 --> 01:02:51,747
- Well, everybody loves that one, chief.
- Oh, everybody.

930
01:02:51,915 --> 01:02:54,750
♪ Happy talk

931
01:02:54,918 --> 01:02:57,920
♪ Keep talking happy talk

932
01:02:58,922 --> 01:03:02,550
♪ Talk about things you like to do

933
01:03:09,391 --> 01:03:12,017
Mr. Korman. Welcome back
to the Kauai Club.

934
01:03:12,143 --> 01:03:14,937
- Great to see you again.
- Thanks. How are you?

935
01:03:15,105 --> 01:03:16,397
Real good. Doin' real good.

936
01:03:16,523 --> 01:03:18,274
This is Betsy.
This is my friend Nahoo.

937
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:21,277
- Pleasure to meet you.
- Nahoo, Betsy. See you.

938
01:03:21,444 --> 01:03:25,030
Bye-bye. Striking resemblance
to the first Mrs. Korman.

939
01:03:25,574 --> 01:03:28,742
♪ Bali Ha'i

940
01:03:30,745 --> 01:03:32,997
♪ Will call you

941
01:03:34,082 --> 01:03:36,208
♪ On the wind

942
01:03:36,334 --> 01:03:39,128
(whistling)

943
01:03:39,296 --> 01:03:41,422
♪ Of the sea

944
01:03:42,132 --> 01:03:44,300
♪ In your heart

945
01:03:44,426 --> 01:03:46,468
- Where's the bathroom?
- ♪ You hear it call you

946
01:03:46,595 --> 01:03:48,804
- Over there.
- Gotta get out of here!

947
01:03:48,972 --> 01:03:52,683
♪ Come to me
Come to me

948
01:03:54,686 --> 01:03:57,646
Orman getting senile.
Used to do only one number.

949
01:03:57,772 --> 01:03:59,940
- Get me to a phone.
- Now?

950
01:04:00,066 --> 01:04:02,192
Right now.
You have a problem with that?

951
01:04:02,319 --> 01:04:06,822
No, no. Just, on this side,
so many beautiful things to see.

952
01:04:06,990 --> 01:04:08,157
- Really?
- Yeah.

953
01:04:08,283 --> 01:04:11,118
We got the five reflecting pools
of Maaoma.

954
01:04:11,244 --> 01:04:13,162
The five pools are here?

955
01:04:13,330 --> 01:04:14,705
- Yeah.
- Jesus!

956
01:04:14,831 --> 01:04:16,957
- Come. We go.
- What are we waiting for?

957
01:04:17,083 --> 01:04:19,501
- Oh, shit!
- What?

958
01:04:19,669 --> 01:04:22,046
My keys must have fallen out
when I was in the bathroom.

959
01:04:22,172 --> 01:04:25,174
- Could you do me a monster favor?
- No worry nothing. I get 'em.

960
01:04:25,342 --> 01:04:26,842
You're the best.

961
01:04:27,010 --> 01:04:29,428
- Everybody here is so friendly.
- Hey!

962
01:04:32,974 --> 01:04:34,516
(dog barking)

963
01:04:35,602 --> 01:04:37,269
(car starts)

964
01:04:46,112 --> 01:04:47,529
(Tommy) Don't say anything.

965
01:04:48,698 --> 01:04:50,115
This wasn't Donna's?

966
01:04:51,034 --> 01:04:53,494
What? God, no.

967
01:04:55,497 --> 01:04:57,081
This is, uh, Betsy's.

968
01:04:59,125 --> 01:05:00,751
It's so beautiful.

969
01:05:01,461 --> 01:05:03,128
Really, I mean...

970
01:05:03,254 --> 01:05:06,465
I've never gotten
anything remotely like this.

971
01:05:06,591 --> 01:05:09,551
I just... I can't accept it.

972
01:05:11,346 --> 01:05:14,139
I want to marry you.
I mean, like, tomorrow.

973
01:05:15,308 --> 01:05:17,267
I can't just marry you.

974
01:05:17,394 --> 01:05:19,019
Why not?
'Cause we just met?

975
01:05:20,063 --> 01:05:21,689
Well, yes.

976
01:05:21,815 --> 01:05:25,234
Look... Just listen to me.

977
01:05:25,402 --> 01:05:28,570
You know, life is so...
what... very short.

978
01:05:28,738 --> 01:05:31,031
We all think too much.

979
01:05:31,157 --> 01:05:34,785
We don't act on our,
you know, impulses.

980
01:05:35,537 --> 01:05:38,038
Korman's address is near Kapaa?

981
01:05:38,164 --> 01:05:42,001
Is it "Kapa-a-a" or "Kapa-a-a-a"?

982
01:05:42,127 --> 01:05:45,504
Is it two "A"s?
Is it A-A-A or A-A?

983
01:05:45,630 --> 01:05:47,589
Two "A"s. OK, thank you.

984
01:05:47,716 --> 01:05:49,049
No, I'm in Waimea.

985
01:05:49,175 --> 01:05:52,261
Listen... I have to get back
to my real life.

986
01:05:52,387 --> 01:05:54,805
This is just way too much
for me to handle.

987
01:05:56,766 --> 01:05:59,018
- Betsy, I love you.
- Tommy...

988
01:05:59,936 --> 01:06:03,188
Oh. I want you in my life.
I want to be married.

989
01:06:04,566 --> 01:06:07,192
- I can't marry you like this.
- Like what?

990
01:06:07,318 --> 01:06:09,945
Like this.
Like just jumping into it.

991
01:06:10,071 --> 01:06:12,573
It just doesn't make any sense,
and there's Jack, too.

992
01:06:12,699 --> 01:06:15,617
I can't just turn around
and marry someone else.

993
01:06:15,785 --> 01:06:18,203
There's stuff to work out with him.
There's feelings there.

994
01:06:21,958 --> 01:06:23,083
What?

995
01:06:26,212 --> 01:06:28,213
The man put you up
in a card game.

996
01:06:29,299 --> 01:06:31,383
No, not really.
You made an arrangement.

997
01:06:32,385 --> 01:06:34,261
I wanted cash. He put you up.

998
01:06:35,889 --> 01:06:37,806
What are you talking about?

999
01:06:38,975 --> 01:06:41,560
(Jack) Mr. Korman and Miss Nolan
are where exactly?

1000
01:06:41,686 --> 01:06:44,354
The Kauai Club.
It's about 20 miles down this road.

1001
01:06:44,481 --> 01:06:47,649
- Thanks very much.
- Are you a friend of Dad's or Betsy's?

1002
01:06:47,776 --> 01:06:49,318
Both, actually.

1003
01:06:49,486 --> 01:06:51,403
They're really great together.

1004
01:06:51,529 --> 01:06:53,322
It's so good to see Chris's dad in love.

1005
01:06:53,490 --> 01:06:56,158
Yeah, well, that's just
so wonderful to hear.

1006
01:06:56,284 --> 01:06:58,619
- OK.
- Goodbye.

1007
01:06:58,745 --> 01:07:01,997
I thought that it was your idea.
You told me that you arranged a game.

1008
01:07:02,123 --> 01:07:05,501
- You saw me in the lobby...
- Yes, honey. Listen.

1009
01:07:05,668 --> 01:07:08,170
I told you that to protect you.

1010
01:07:09,672 --> 01:07:11,673
Because I love you so very much.

1011
01:07:13,676 --> 01:07:15,761
Honey, and the truth was so...

1012
01:07:16,930 --> 01:07:18,472
...horrible!

1013
01:07:19,516 --> 01:07:20,766
It embarrassed me.

1014
01:07:21,643 --> 01:07:23,018
He put you up like a...

1015
01:07:23,186 --> 01:07:25,687
...like a ring, like a watch.

1016
01:07:25,814 --> 01:07:27,606
That's how cold it was.

1017
01:07:27,732 --> 01:07:29,608
I can't believe it.
Maybe he was frantic.

1018
01:07:29,734 --> 01:07:32,861
Listen, people get frightened.
They do crazy things.

1019
01:07:33,029 --> 01:07:35,364
He was so terrified
of marrying you.

1020
01:07:35,490 --> 01:07:38,909
Come on, that's unfair.
He didn't have $65,000.

1021
01:07:39,035 --> 01:07:40,577
What...

1022
01:07:41,538 --> 01:07:43,539
That's what he owed you.

1023
01:07:46,209 --> 01:07:48,210
He owed me $3,000.

1024
01:07:50,713 --> 01:07:52,047
What?

1025
01:07:53,883 --> 01:07:55,342
Honey, look.

1026
01:07:56,386 --> 01:07:59,096
The man's a head case. He's a head case.

1027
01:07:59,222 --> 01:08:01,765
But we all make mistakes.
Life goes on.

1028
01:08:01,891 --> 01:08:04,059
He did this for $3,000?

1029
01:08:04,227 --> 01:08:06,895
Honey, don't. Please, darling.

1030
01:08:07,063 --> 01:08:08,981
Don't torture yourself like this.

1031
01:08:09,107 --> 01:08:11,316
Let's just fly to Vegas and...

1032
01:08:11,442 --> 01:08:13,944
...get married
and go on with our lives.

1033
01:08:14,863 --> 01:08:16,864
I need to be alone for awhile.

1034
01:08:30,420 --> 01:08:31,920
Keep it close by.

1035
01:08:43,808 --> 01:08:45,267
(Jack) Betsy!

1036
01:08:48,146 --> 01:08:50,272
- Betsy!
- (waves crashing loudly)

1037
01:08:51,608 --> 01:08:52,608
Betsy!

1038
01:08:54,110 --> 01:08:55,194
(grunts)

1039
01:08:58,323 --> 01:08:59,615
Get off!

1040
01:08:59,782 --> 01:09:02,034
Get off me!

1041
01:09:02,160 --> 01:09:03,952
What the hell are you doing here?
We had a deal.

1042
01:09:04,078 --> 01:09:06,205
We never said Hawaii.
Get off me.

1043
01:09:06,331 --> 01:09:08,415
We never didn't say Hawaii.

1044
01:09:08,541 --> 01:09:10,500
Look, you want to stay
on the island, fine.

1045
01:09:10,627 --> 01:09:13,587
But you stay the hell away
from her or give me 65 thousand.

1046
01:09:13,713 --> 01:09:14,713
I've got it.

1047
01:09:14,839 --> 01:09:16,340
I brought it with me.

1048
01:09:17,217 --> 01:09:18,634
No. That's bullshit.

1049
01:09:18,760 --> 01:09:21,303
You never wanted the money.
You wanted her!

1050
01:09:22,805 --> 01:09:25,307
Get off me! Somebody!

1051
01:09:25,433 --> 01:09:27,142
Help! Get off me!

1052
01:09:27,268 --> 01:09:29,102
- (Jack) Betsy!
- (Tommy) He's crazy!

1053
01:09:30,271 --> 01:09:31,396
Betsy!

1054
01:09:32,690 --> 01:09:34,983
- Get him out of here!
- Betsy!

1055
01:09:35,693 --> 01:09:37,152
(faint) Betsy!

1056
01:09:40,114 --> 01:09:42,032
(grunting)

1057
01:09:46,621 --> 01:09:48,789
Come on. Don't.
You're making a big mistake.

1058
01:09:49,624 --> 01:09:53,001
Listen to me.
My girl's out there. My wife!

1059
01:10:02,971 --> 01:10:04,221
You OK?

1060
01:10:05,306 --> 01:10:07,474
- That was the weirdest thing.
- What?

1061
01:10:07,600 --> 01:10:09,268
It was like Wuthering Heights.

1062
01:10:09,394 --> 01:10:11,645
I thought I heard my name
being called in the wind.

1063
01:10:11,771 --> 01:10:13,647
It sounded like Jack.
Can you believe that?

1064
01:10:13,773 --> 01:10:18,568
Yeah. I used to think
that I heard Donna calling...

1065
01:10:18,695 --> 01:10:20,404
Almost shouting.

1066
01:10:21,364 --> 01:10:22,823
It's very spooky.

1067
01:10:23,908 --> 01:10:27,119
It's the shape of the rocks
or something. It echoes.

1068
01:10:27,245 --> 01:10:29,329
- It's so strange.
- Yeah.

1069
01:10:33,710 --> 01:10:35,627
So what do you think?

1070
01:10:37,171 --> 01:10:39,506
I'm gonna want children very soon.

1071
01:10:45,305 --> 01:10:47,389
You just tell me when, sweetheart.

1072
01:10:47,515 --> 01:10:51,643
Having children
with you would be heaven.

1073
01:10:52,854 --> 01:10:54,896
Then let's do it. I want to.

1074
01:10:55,815 --> 01:10:59,026
Are you sure this is not
a reaction to what I told you?

1075
01:10:59,152 --> 01:11:01,987
No, no, I want
to get on with my life, Tommy.

1076
01:11:02,113 --> 01:11:03,530
I want to get married.

1077
01:11:04,949 --> 01:11:05,949
To me?

1078
01:11:07,493 --> 01:11:09,077
Yes.

1079
01:11:11,831 --> 01:11:13,290
(sighs)

1080
01:11:15,710 --> 01:11:17,294
I'm shakin' like a leaf.

1081
01:11:22,633 --> 01:11:24,551
(♪ Elvis Presley: Jailhouse Rock)

1082
01:11:39,609 --> 01:11:40,984
(shouts)

1083
01:11:41,110 --> 01:11:43,445
Look, I have to make
a phone call now!

1084
01:11:44,238 --> 01:11:47,783
You're kidding me!
You're in a Hawaiian clink?

1085
01:11:48,951 --> 01:11:51,703
- Vito, you believe that?
- Uh-uh. Uh-uh.

1086
01:11:51,829 --> 01:11:53,580
(Sally) Vito's in the chair.
He can't believe it.

1087
01:11:53,706 --> 01:11:56,249
Listen. The bail is five grand.

1088
01:11:56,376 --> 01:11:58,251
OK, let me work on it.

1089
01:11:58,378 --> 01:11:59,628
But, Jack, listen to me.

1090
01:11:59,754 --> 01:12:02,130
Make sure you ask approval
to leave the state.

1091
01:12:02,256 --> 01:12:04,299
Otherwise you'll be stuck there
even if you make bail.

1092
01:12:04,425 --> 01:12:08,053
OK, but, Sally,
as fast as you can, please.

1093
01:12:08,179 --> 01:12:10,639
Just seeing her there,
staring at the ocean...

1094
01:12:11,599 --> 01:12:13,100
I know that look, man.

1095
01:12:13,226 --> 01:12:15,310
She's doing some serious thinking.

1096
01:12:15,436 --> 01:12:17,187
Well? Ready?

1097
01:12:17,313 --> 01:12:19,731
This is really such a great spot.

1098
01:12:19,857 --> 01:12:21,858
We'll be back real soon.

1099
01:12:30,118 --> 01:12:33,078
- Thanks.
- I want to say one thing, ma'am.

1100
01:12:33,204 --> 01:12:35,330
Anybody who would put you up
for $3,000...

1101
01:12:35,456 --> 01:12:37,624
Hey, Niko,
what's the matter with you?

1102
01:12:37,750 --> 01:12:40,460
- Sorry.
- That's all right. Really.

1103
01:12:40,586 --> 01:12:42,587
- (Niko) Sorry.
- Jesus.

1104
01:12:46,008 --> 01:12:47,008
Perfect.

1105
01:12:48,845 --> 01:12:50,512
(♪ Jailhouse Rock continues)

1106
01:13:04,861 --> 01:13:07,654
Don't tell me
you still want the cab fare.

1107
01:13:07,780 --> 01:13:12,284
Nah. I dropped the charges.
I feel sorry for you, man.

1108
01:13:12,410 --> 01:13:16,037
I don't want your pity.
Just take me to Korman's house. Korman.

1109
01:13:17,748 --> 01:13:19,624
No do you any good.

1110
01:13:19,750 --> 01:13:21,835
Him, your girlfriend,
both went back Vegas.

1111
01:13:21,961 --> 01:13:22,961
Gonna get married.

1112
01:13:23,921 --> 01:13:25,547
Married?

1113
01:13:25,715 --> 01:13:27,299
(mouthing) Married.

1114
01:13:32,388 --> 01:13:33,680
(Mahi) Hey, Jack.

1115
01:13:34,891 --> 01:13:36,558
Jack, Jack.

1116
01:13:37,518 --> 01:13:39,269
- Good luck, brother. Hey.
- Thanks.

1117
01:13:40,062 --> 01:13:42,314
Always remember:
(speaks Hawaiian)

1118
01:13:47,069 --> 01:13:50,739
It means, "Always have the good words
come out of your mouth."

1119
01:13:50,907 --> 01:13:53,575
That just doesn't help me at all,
but I appreciate the thought.

1120
01:13:53,743 --> 01:13:55,118
(Mahi) Aloha, brother!

1121
01:13:55,369 --> 01:13:57,245
(woman on PA)

1122
01:14:01,250 --> 01:14:02,250
Hello.

1123
01:14:02,418 --> 01:14:04,211
I gotta get on
the next flight out of here.

1124
01:14:05,379 --> 01:14:08,256
The next flight out of here
goes nonstop to...

1125
01:14:08,424 --> 01:14:09,716
Auckland, New Zealand.

1126
01:14:09,842 --> 01:14:12,719
New Zealand?
No, I gotta get to the States.

1127
01:14:12,845 --> 01:14:14,262
We are a state.

1128
01:14:15,097 --> 01:14:17,933
The mainland, OK?
I gotta get to Vegas.

1129
01:14:18,935 --> 01:14:22,604
Well, the Los Angeles flight
left Honolulu 20 minutes ago.

1130
01:14:22,730 --> 01:14:23,939
Shit!

1131
01:14:24,106 --> 01:14:27,859
- When's the next flight out of here?
- Tonight at 8:30.

1132
01:14:28,319 --> 01:14:29,653
(exhales deeply)

1133
01:14:29,779 --> 01:14:32,739
Ma'am, I'll be sucking
on an exhaust pipe by then.

1134
01:14:32,865 --> 01:14:37,077
Just get me anywhere where I can get
a connecting flight to Las Vegas.

1135
01:14:37,912 --> 01:14:39,788
(♪ Trisha Yearwood:
(You're the) Devil in Disguise)

1136
01:14:52,051 --> 01:14:54,886
You know, you shouldn't live...
(stammers)... where Donna lived.

1137
01:14:55,012 --> 01:14:57,013
I don't think that's fair.

1138
01:14:57,932 --> 01:14:59,933
So, I was thinkin'...

1139
01:15:00,977 --> 01:15:04,396
...we buy a place
in Westchester or Connecticut.

1140
01:15:04,522 --> 01:15:06,523
I can't think about that yet.

1141
01:15:07,733 --> 01:15:10,735
That's OK. I'll think about it.

1142
01:15:10,861 --> 01:15:13,822
You sit back and you relax.
OK, sweetheart?

1143
01:15:16,450 --> 01:15:18,493
(woman on PA)

1144
01:15:19,704 --> 01:15:21,746
Congratulations to the two of you.

1145
01:15:21,872 --> 01:15:23,331
Penthouse A is ready.

1146
01:15:23,457 --> 01:15:25,542
That's great, Bud. I appreciate it.

1147
01:15:28,004 --> 01:15:30,046
Mr. Korman's getting married.

1148
01:15:34,969 --> 01:15:37,304
Don't take too long with the makeup.

1149
01:15:37,430 --> 01:15:39,347
I like you au naturel.

1150
01:15:40,933 --> 01:15:42,183
Don't worry.

1151
01:15:43,144 --> 01:15:45,145
You don't need any, anyway.

1152
01:15:55,197 --> 01:15:57,115
He left Kauai.

1153
01:15:57,241 --> 01:15:59,451
But he couldn't get an LA flight.

1154
01:15:59,577 --> 01:16:00,910
So where is he?

1155
01:16:01,037 --> 01:16:03,663
- San Jose.
- San Jose...

1156
01:16:04,874 --> 01:16:06,833
San Jose. Well...

1157
01:16:06,959 --> 01:16:09,461
Who do we know
at the airport in San Jose?

1158
01:16:09,587 --> 01:16:12,213
- Frankie Cargo.
- Give him a phone call.

1159
01:16:12,381 --> 01:16:13,882
Go on.

1160
01:16:14,008 --> 01:16:15,550
(woman on PA)

1161
01:16:18,471 --> 01:16:20,347
- This flight is history?
- (man) Yes.

1162
01:16:20,473 --> 01:16:22,307
Apparently there's
bad weather in El Paso.

1163
01:16:22,433 --> 01:16:25,143
- Hail the size of golf balls.
- I don't care about El Paso.

1164
01:16:25,269 --> 01:16:27,604
- How do I get to Vegas?
- Well, let's see.

1165
01:16:27,730 --> 01:16:30,732
There's a 9:00pm flight
into Los Angeles.

1166
01:16:30,900 --> 01:16:33,652
It arrives at 10:15...

1167
01:16:33,778 --> 01:16:37,822
And then you can just take
a 12:35 flight into Vegas.

1168
01:16:37,948 --> 01:16:39,949
- That's it?
- Until tomorrow morning, yes.

1169
01:16:40,076 --> 01:16:41,076
Oh, man.

1170
01:16:41,243 --> 01:16:45,080
(woman on PA) Attention, Pakistani,
Indian and Malaysian Elvises:

1171
01:16:45,206 --> 01:16:48,500
Your bus to the Grand Canyon
is leaving in eight minutes.

1172
01:16:48,626 --> 01:16:51,294
(Jack on machine)
...when the beeper goes off. Thanks.

1173
01:16:51,420 --> 01:16:53,421
(machine beeps)

1174
01:16:53,547 --> 01:16:57,133
Hi, Jack, it's me.
I'm back in Vegas with Tommy.

1175
01:16:57,259 --> 01:17:01,221
I tried you when I was in Hawaii,
but you were never there, so...

1176
01:17:02,264 --> 01:17:04,974
Look, Jack, here's the thing. I don't
know why you lied to me about the game.

1177
01:17:05,101 --> 01:17:07,769
All right? I don't know,
but I suppose I can guess.

1178
01:17:07,937 --> 01:17:10,021
The worst part about this
is I don't know where you are.

1179
01:17:10,147 --> 01:17:12,065
I don't know and I can't
speak to you direc...

1180
01:17:12,191 --> 01:17:13,608
(machine beeps)

1181
01:17:14,985 --> 01:17:16,903
(woman on PA) Ladies and gentlemen.
For your convenience,

1182
01:17:17,029 --> 01:17:19,280
we have immediate seating available...

1183
01:17:20,783 --> 01:17:22,951
I'll go crack open the champagne.

1184
01:17:23,119 --> 01:17:25,286
Are you always
going to keep me waiting?

1185
01:17:25,413 --> 01:17:26,913
That's a joke.

1186
01:17:27,998 --> 01:17:29,958
You can keep me waiting anytime.

1187
01:17:31,752 --> 01:17:34,754
Vegas! Anybody going to Vegas?

1188
01:17:34,880 --> 01:17:36,965
Las Vegas! Anybody!

1189
01:17:37,133 --> 01:17:38,925
Anybody, Vegas!

1190
01:17:39,051 --> 01:17:42,178
Are you guys going to Vegas
by any chance?

1191
01:17:42,304 --> 01:17:44,305
Yeah! We sure are. You need a lift?

1192
01:17:44,432 --> 01:17:47,100
- Oh, desperately.
- You done this before, son?

1193
01:17:48,227 --> 01:17:50,145
Yeah, yeah, sure. I love
these little planes. They're great.

1194
01:17:50,271 --> 01:17:53,064
Oh, come on. Hop aboard.
You'll have a good time.

1195
01:17:53,190 --> 01:17:54,899
We got a new one, boys.

1196
01:17:55,025 --> 01:17:57,152
Come on in there.
Let's go. Let's go!

1197
01:17:59,739 --> 01:18:01,322
Could we talk?

1198
01:18:01,449 --> 01:18:03,950
- Sure, we could talk.
- No, back inside.

1199
01:18:05,369 --> 01:18:06,661
Please?

1200
01:18:09,790 --> 01:18:11,666
(woman on PA)

1201
01:18:26,348 --> 01:18:27,974
- (excited chatter)
- You ready, Zeke?

1202
01:18:28,100 --> 01:18:30,059
- Ready!
- (all shouting)

1203
01:18:30,186 --> 01:18:33,354
Hey, all right.
What's your cape size, son?

1204
01:18:33,522 --> 01:18:36,566
- What's my cape size?
- Uh-huh.

1205
01:18:36,692 --> 01:18:37,692
Forty regular.

1206
01:18:37,860 --> 01:18:39,652
What's with the parachutes?

1207
01:18:40,988 --> 01:18:44,282
You're gonna find out as soon as
you strap one on, I guarantee you.

1208
01:18:44,408 --> 01:18:47,869
For such a short flight, it seems
like you're being overcautious.

1209
01:18:48,037 --> 01:18:50,413
I don't know. It's just a hunch, but...

1210
01:18:50,539 --> 01:18:52,707
Son, we're skydivin'.

1211
01:18:53,375 --> 01:18:55,210
You're skydiving?

1212
01:18:55,377 --> 01:18:58,213
We're the Flying Elvises,
Utah chapter.

1213
01:18:58,380 --> 01:19:00,924
Roy Bacon, director, at your service.

1214
01:19:01,050 --> 01:19:02,926
Listen, if you could just drop me.

1215
01:19:03,052 --> 01:19:05,178
- (all laughing)
- Oh, yeah, we'll sure drop you!

1216
01:19:11,101 --> 01:19:12,727
This is a panic attack.

1217
01:19:12,895 --> 01:19:15,230
Why does it have to be so soon?

1218
01:19:15,397 --> 01:19:20,068
(stammers) Well, honey, you know,
I told you there comes a time when...

1219
01:19:20,236 --> 01:19:21,986
I'm not ready.

1220
01:19:22,112 --> 01:19:24,489
Nah. You just think you're not ready.

1221
01:19:24,615 --> 01:19:26,741
No, I'm not ready.

1222
01:19:26,909 --> 01:19:30,537
I say we wait a few weeks.
You know? A month.

1223
01:19:30,663 --> 01:19:33,081
We, we get to know each other better.

1224
01:19:37,586 --> 01:19:41,089
OK... Look, I'll give you
half a million dollars

1225
01:19:41,257 --> 01:19:42,423
if you marry me today. Cash.

1226
01:19:42,591 --> 01:19:46,803
And if things don't work out,
we split up, you keep the money.

1227
01:19:48,264 --> 01:19:49,430
You're joking.

1228
01:19:49,598 --> 01:19:52,100
About money, I, I neverjoke.

1229
01:19:52,935 --> 01:19:54,936
Screw you.

1230
01:19:57,523 --> 01:20:02,068
Please. Don't ever turn
your back on me. Ever.

1231
01:20:02,194 --> 01:20:03,778
Weekend is over.

1232
01:20:04,864 --> 01:20:06,865
Don't grab me like that.

1233
01:20:08,284 --> 01:20:10,994
You are being rude to me.

1234
01:20:11,912 --> 01:20:16,207
In the lobby of the Bally Hotel,
you are being rude.

1235
01:20:17,668 --> 01:20:18,960
Get out of my sight.

1236
01:20:19,587 --> 01:20:20,670
(Tommy) Hey!

1237
01:20:22,256 --> 01:20:24,966
A million. Now, be a realist.

1238
01:20:25,092 --> 01:20:27,093
This is a no-lose deal for you.

1239
01:20:27,219 --> 01:20:29,220
I get a million dollars?

1240
01:20:29,972 --> 01:20:31,472
Yeah. That's correct.

1241
01:20:32,474 --> 01:20:33,766
You're unbelievable.

1242
01:20:33,893 --> 01:20:37,270
It would be very irresponsible
of you to turn this down.

1243
01:20:37,396 --> 01:20:39,063
- Tommy...
- Hey.

1244
01:20:40,190 --> 01:20:42,066
Your answer...

1245
01:20:42,192 --> 01:20:43,484
...is yes.

1246
01:20:45,863 --> 01:20:47,989
I have to go to the bathroom.

1247
01:20:50,034 --> 01:20:52,160
OK, come on.
I'll go with you.

1248
01:20:52,286 --> 01:20:54,537
I need to be alone
for a couple of minutes.

1249
01:20:58,626 --> 01:21:02,420
OK. You got five minutes,
and then we get married.

1250
01:21:02,546 --> 01:21:03,838
Listen.

1251
01:21:06,884 --> 01:21:10,053
You said, "Yes, I will marry you."

1252
01:21:11,513 --> 01:21:12,805
That's a promise.

1253
01:21:15,267 --> 01:21:18,269
When people make promises
to Tommy Korman, they keep 'em.

1254
01:21:19,480 --> 01:21:20,813
You understand?

1255
01:21:21,899 --> 01:21:24,108
- Yes, I do. Yes.
- Hmm?

1256
01:21:29,531 --> 01:21:31,157
You got five minutes.

1257
01:21:42,378 --> 01:21:43,920
She's comin' up here?

1258
01:21:45,547 --> 01:21:46,714
I thought you left already.

1259
01:21:46,882 --> 01:21:49,175
No. Just stay close to her,
all right?

1260
01:21:54,181 --> 01:21:55,348
Where is he?

1261
01:21:57,685 --> 01:21:59,477
(♪ Travis Tritt: Burning Love)

1262
01:22:03,983 --> 01:22:08,069
(mouthing words to Elvis song)

1263
01:22:17,329 --> 01:22:20,289
Ooh, boy, that music
gets the adrenaline going, don't it?

1264
01:22:20,416 --> 01:22:22,792
- We jump out at what altitude?
- Three thousand feet.

1265
01:22:23,877 --> 01:22:26,421
And these chutes are foolproof, right?

1266
01:22:26,588 --> 01:22:28,506
Well, as the King his own self said...

1267
01:22:28,632 --> 01:22:30,633
they ain't nothin' in this
whole wide world foolproof,

1268
01:22:30,759 --> 01:22:33,553
exceptin' Coupe DeVilles and hookers!

1269
01:22:35,889 --> 01:22:38,099
Let me get this straight.
I pull this?

1270
01:22:38,267 --> 01:22:40,768
No, boy, you pull
the other one first,

1271
01:22:40,894 --> 01:22:42,437
that being your main chute.

1272
01:22:42,563 --> 01:22:46,107
Then if that chute don't open,
you reach over and pull the red one,

1273
01:22:46,275 --> 01:22:48,568
that there being your auxiliary chute.

1274
01:22:48,694 --> 01:22:50,278
Yellow, then red. Yellow, then red.

1275
01:22:50,404 --> 01:22:52,822
- (impersonator) You got it.
- (Jack) OK, OK. Now...

1276
01:22:52,948 --> 01:22:56,451
lf, by any chance, I get flustered
when I'm hurtling through space...

1277
01:22:56,618 --> 01:22:58,536
and I pull the red one first?

1278
01:22:58,662 --> 01:23:01,581
Oh! Then you gonna wind up
lookin' like a well-done chili burger.

1279
01:23:01,707 --> 01:23:04,000
They gonna have to
shovel you into a coffin.

1280
01:23:06,837 --> 01:23:09,464
But you can do it, son. You can do it!

1281
01:23:09,631 --> 01:23:13,342
All right, fellers.
It's just about show time!

1282
01:23:13,469 --> 01:23:15,470
Yellow, then red.
Yellow, then red.

1283
01:23:41,288 --> 01:23:42,663
She never came up.

1284
01:23:45,250 --> 01:23:47,376
- Go find her.
- Where?

1285
01:23:48,545 --> 01:23:50,922
I don't know. Try outside.

1286
01:23:51,048 --> 01:23:54,675
(man on PA) Six minutes until the Flying
Elvises make their historic jump.

1287
01:23:59,640 --> 01:24:02,975
- Elvises, rise!
- (all hollering)

1288
01:24:05,687 --> 01:24:07,855
(repeating) Yellow, then red.
Yellow, then red.

1289
01:24:07,981 --> 01:24:10,399
Yellow, then red. Yellow, then red.
Yellow, then red. Yellow, then red.

1290
01:24:16,323 --> 01:24:17,323
(alarm sounds)

1291
01:24:19,243 --> 01:24:20,952
(Buddy) Where you going?

1292
01:24:21,078 --> 01:24:23,037
(shouting, pounding on door)

1293
01:24:23,747 --> 01:24:26,707
(man on PA) Ladies and gentlemen
Roy Bacon and his Flying Elvises

1294
01:24:26,834 --> 01:24:28,209
are approaching Bally's.

1295
01:24:28,335 --> 01:24:30,795
- All eyes to the sky!
- (crowd chanting) Elvis!

1296
01:24:30,921 --> 01:24:32,547
(staff speaking Spanish)

1297
01:24:40,055 --> 01:24:41,973
(crowd applauding)

1298
01:24:46,186 --> 01:24:47,812
(man) OK, OK.

1299
01:24:54,653 --> 01:24:56,821
- (woman on PA)
- (chatter)

1300
01:25:02,828 --> 01:25:05,204
She's somewhere in the basement.

1301
01:25:05,330 --> 01:25:07,415
So, tell me, what are you
doing in the lobby?

1302
01:25:07,541 --> 01:25:10,334
- I'm keeping you informed.
- Go get her! Go get her!

1303
01:25:13,380 --> 01:25:14,714
Moron.

1304
01:25:16,258 --> 01:25:18,176
(man on PA) Ladies and gentlemen,
the Flying Elvises

1305
01:25:18,302 --> 01:25:22,221
have entered Las Vegas airspace
and will jump in one minute!

1306
01:25:22,639 --> 01:25:23,639
One minute!

1307
01:25:33,275 --> 01:25:37,445
Elvises, light your fires!

1308
01:25:39,781 --> 01:25:41,282
Betsy! Betsy! Betsy! Betsy!

1309
01:25:41,408 --> 01:25:43,075
That's it.
Look at them up there!

1310
01:25:48,498 --> 01:25:52,960
Elvises, head 'em up
and move 'em out!

1311
01:25:53,128 --> 01:25:54,587
(all shouting)

1312
01:25:54,713 --> 01:25:56,672
(♪ Elvis Presley: That's All Right)

1313
01:26:06,683 --> 01:26:08,100
(man on PA) Here they come!

1314
01:26:08,977 --> 01:26:10,978
Excuse me.

1315
01:26:11,104 --> 01:26:14,899
(man on PA) Never before have so many
Elvises been airborne!

1316
01:26:21,448 --> 01:26:24,116
Let's give them
a real Las Vegas welcome

1317
01:26:24,243 --> 01:26:26,994
and pray that they make it
safely to Earth.

1318
01:26:29,206 --> 01:26:32,959
You know you pull the red one,
then the yellow one!

1319
01:26:33,085 --> 01:26:35,544
No, he said yellow, then red!

1320
01:26:35,671 --> 01:26:37,171
No! He was just kidding!

1321
01:26:37,297 --> 01:26:38,506
Lyle, come on, Lyle!

1322
01:26:38,674 --> 01:26:40,758
- Good luck!
- Wait a minute!

1323
01:26:42,469 --> 01:26:44,553
- I was just kidding.
- You were or Roy was?

1324
01:26:44,680 --> 01:26:45,846
He was.

1325
01:26:48,850 --> 01:26:50,726
(man on PA) Our brave Elvises of the sky

1326
01:26:50,852 --> 01:26:53,771
are wearing specially designed
electric jumpsuits

1327
01:26:53,897 --> 01:26:57,316
made to the King's
own specifications.

1328
01:26:57,442 --> 01:27:01,445
Each suit is valued
at over $10,000.

1329
01:27:04,032 --> 01:27:05,616
Here they come!

1330
01:27:05,742 --> 01:27:07,910
They're crossing the Dunes.

1331
01:27:08,036 --> 01:27:11,038
Then they're headed home to Bally's.

1332
01:27:19,548 --> 01:27:21,590
One last time! Yellow, then red?

1333
01:27:22,926 --> 01:27:24,677
(screaming)

1334
01:27:25,929 --> 01:27:27,513
Betsy! Betsy! Betsy! Betsy!

1335
01:27:36,732 --> 01:27:39,233
Yee-haw!

1336
01:27:40,652 --> 01:27:42,403
Roy Bacon has opened his chute.

1337
01:27:42,571 --> 01:27:44,322
Only one to go!

1338
01:27:46,241 --> 01:27:48,326
Yellow! Red! Pow!

1339
01:27:49,828 --> 01:27:52,204
The last chute is open!

1340
01:27:55,375 --> 01:27:58,294
That's good. That's great.

1341
01:27:58,420 --> 01:28:00,212
I'm not gonna die.

1342
01:28:02,132 --> 01:28:03,299
Don't look down.

1343
01:28:06,553 --> 01:28:09,347
(man on PA)
Here comes our first Elvis to Earth.

1344
01:28:09,473 --> 01:28:12,516
Tommy Joe Smithers
of Provo, Utah.

1345
01:28:14,102 --> 01:28:17,605
Our second Elvis,
from Elko, Nevada...

1346
01:28:17,773 --> 01:28:18,981
Walter Peeblinger!

1347
01:28:20,609 --> 01:28:23,569
God, don't let me land
on anything sharp.

1348
01:28:23,695 --> 01:28:26,739
Left, toggle left.
Right, toggle right.

1349
01:28:28,033 --> 01:28:29,950
The wind currents are picking up!

1350
01:28:31,119 --> 01:28:33,829
Watch it up there,
brave Elvises of the sky!

1351
01:28:33,955 --> 01:28:34,955
(Jack) Steady, boy.

1352
01:28:36,208 --> 01:28:37,416
Here we go.

1353
01:28:38,293 --> 01:28:39,960
That's good. OK.

1354
01:28:40,087 --> 01:28:43,839
Here they come.
From Tucson, Billy Braker!

1355
01:28:43,965 --> 01:28:47,551
From Salt Lake City,
Lyle Davis and Vern Poole.

1356
01:28:47,677 --> 01:28:51,138
And our newest Flying Elvis
from New York City...

1357
01:28:51,264 --> 01:28:54,809
making his maiden jump,
Jack Singer!

1358
01:28:54,935 --> 01:28:57,937
Let's give a real
Las Vegas welcome

1359
01:28:58,063 --> 01:29:02,316
for our heroic young man,
Jack Singer!

1360
01:29:05,320 --> 01:29:09,448
Welcome to Earth,
brave Elvises!

1361
01:29:09,574 --> 01:29:11,117
- Miss, stay back.
- Please.

1362
01:29:15,956 --> 01:29:16,956
Jack!

1363
01:29:18,166 --> 01:29:20,084
- Betsy!
- Jack!

1364
01:29:27,759 --> 01:29:28,759
Betsy!

1365
01:29:32,514 --> 01:29:33,681
Did you marry him?

1366
01:29:33,807 --> 01:29:36,183
(♪ Elvis Presley:
Falling in Love)

1367
01:29:46,987 --> 01:29:50,197
Jack! You jumped out of a plane!

1368
01:29:50,323 --> 01:29:52,700
His kid said you were gonna
marry him today.

1369
01:29:52,868 --> 01:29:54,452
Did you get a job here?

1370
01:29:54,578 --> 01:29:57,496
I couldn't find you.
I didn't know how to reach you.

1371
01:29:57,622 --> 01:30:00,166
I was flying day and night.
I was going everywhere.

1372
01:30:00,292 --> 01:30:04,336
Hawaii, jail... I saw you on the beach.
I was screaming your name.

1373
01:30:04,463 --> 01:30:06,380
He said that was the wind.

1374
01:30:06,548 --> 01:30:08,215
I was so stupid.

1375
01:30:13,096 --> 01:30:14,472
I can't find her.

1376
01:30:16,808 --> 01:30:19,852
It's over. Son of a bitch
jumped out of a plane.

1377
01:30:19,978 --> 01:30:21,061
What?

1378
01:30:22,063 --> 01:30:24,690
He said you only lost 3,000.

1379
01:30:24,816 --> 01:30:26,567
- What?
- And I believed him.

1380
01:30:26,735 --> 01:30:31,238
Then I realized, I said,
"What, am I nuts? I can't marry him."

1381
01:30:33,033 --> 01:30:34,325
(crowd chanting) Elvis!

1382
01:30:36,286 --> 01:30:39,205
And then you jumped
out of a plane for me!

1383
01:30:39,331 --> 01:30:40,748
You could've died.

1384
01:30:40,916 --> 01:30:43,334
I didn't want to live
if I couldn't have you, baby.

1385
01:30:46,546 --> 01:30:48,422
Go take a hike.

1386
01:30:48,548 --> 01:30:50,466
- Now?
- No, next Thursday.

1387
01:30:50,592 --> 01:30:53,052
Yeah, now. Go set up a game.

1388
01:30:53,178 --> 01:30:54,762
I'll just grab a bite.

1389
01:30:56,681 --> 01:30:58,682
- Go!
- All right, all right.

1390
01:30:59,768 --> 01:31:02,269
I dreamt about my mother again
last night.

1391
01:31:02,437 --> 01:31:04,063
Was she vacuuming naked?

1392
01:31:04,189 --> 01:31:06,690
No. She opened her eyes, and I said,

1393
01:31:06,816 --> 01:31:11,153
"Mom, I'm gonna marry that girl,"
and she smiled.

1394
01:31:11,279 --> 01:31:13,447
- (Betsy) Really?
- (Jack) Yeah.

1395
01:31:13,615 --> 01:31:14,949
Of course, she was naked.

1396
01:31:17,577 --> 01:31:20,454
(man) Jack and Betsy,
you have declared your desire

1397
01:31:20,622 --> 01:31:23,290
to unite yourselves
with each other in marriage.

1398
01:31:23,416 --> 01:31:26,085
- This is correct?
- (both) Yes.

1399
01:31:26,211 --> 01:31:27,628
(minister) True matrimony is...

1400
01:31:27,796 --> 01:31:29,964
(♪ Elvis Presley: It's Now orNever)

1401
01:31:39,099 --> 01:31:41,100
(sniffling) Oh.

1402
01:31:45,647 --> 01:31:48,148
Yee-haw! Whoo!

1403
01:31:48,275 --> 01:31:50,150
(all cheering)

1404
01:31:58,410 --> 01:32:00,869
(♪ Billy Joel: All Shook Up)

1405
01:33:09,230 --> 01:33:11,732
(♪ Ricky Van Shelton:
Wear My Ring Around Your Neck)

1406
01:34:22,011 --> 01:34:24,596
(♪ Trisha Yearwood:
(You're the) Devil in Disguise)